  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTC-964 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5103299"> (Completed Example) Template Drop in From TestCase LFWM-VALTC-461 </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">10/17/2025 06:33:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">10/17/2025 06:33:57 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTC-964</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3303526</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">(Completed Example) Template Drop in From TestCase LFWM-VALTC-461</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p><strong>(Actual Name)&nbsp;</strong>Verify the 1.1-meter hazard zone from mower body to hazard boundary (Autonomous Mode)</p> <p><strong>Objective</strong><br> Validate that when an obstacle breaches the 1.1 m hazard boundary, the mower performs a Category 0 e-stop.</p> <p><strong>Scenario (BDD intent)</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p><em>Scenario:</em>&nbsp;Vehicle encounters an obstacle 1.1 m from the outermost fixed point of the mower (“mower body”) to the hazard boundary.</p></li>
        <li><p><em>Given</em>&nbsp;mower in Autonomous mode on approved test map</p></li>
        <li><p><em>When</em>&nbsp;an obstacle intrudes within the 1.1 m hazard boundary</p></li>
        <li><p><em>Then</em>&nbsp;mower executes Category 0 e-stop within ≤ 2.0 s, beacon and audible alarm assert, ActivityState =3D EStopped</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Requirement Traceability</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>JAMA: SAF-HZ-001.1, MOB-ESTOP-CAT0-002</p></li>
        <li><p>Safety Class: SIL-relevant; Category 0 stop</p></li>
        <li><p>Priority: P0 (safety critical)</p></li>
        <li><p>Release Target: R_3.6_2025.09</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Preconditions &amp; Configurations</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>Platform: JD 7500A test unit “Blaze”</p></li>
        <li><p>Firmware/Software: VCU v3.12.4; SMU v2.9.1; Mobius Client v9.3.0; PayloadSvc v5.8.2</p></li>
        <li><p>Mode: Autonomous enabled; wireless e-stop paired/healthy</p></li>
        <li><p>Map/Plan loaded; geofence active; no active faults</p></li>
        <li><p>Battery SOC ≥ 40%</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Environmental Conditions &amp; Infrastructure</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>Test pad: Paved, level ≤ 2° slope; dry surface</p></li>
        <li><p>Weather: 0–25 °C, wind &lt; 8 m/s, no precipitation</p></li>
        <li><p>GNSS: RTK fixed or simulated equivalent; HDOP ≤ 1.2</p></li>
        <li><p>Comms: Uplink/downlink healthy; RSSI ≥ −90 dBm</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Input/Test Data</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>Map: Preston_Pad_HazardZone_v07.json</p></li>
        <li><p>Plan: HZ_Breach_Straight_10m.plan</p></li>
        <li><p>Obstacles (two identical): 40×40×60 cm foam block with rigid core; reflectivity ~medium; ID tags OB-HZ-01, OB-HZ-02</p></li>
        <li><p>Hazard boundary distance: 1.10 m ± 0.05 m from mower body reference</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Instrumentation &amp; Observability</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>Telemetry: ActivityState, StopCategory, BeaconState, AudibleAlarm, VehicleSpeed, GNSS status, ObstacleDetection flag, E-stop reason, timestamps (≥ 10 Hz)</p></li>
        <li><p>High-speed video (≥ 60 fps) side view with distance markers</p></li>
        <li><p>Laser distance meter or calibrated tape for 1.1 m placement (± 1 cm)</p></li>
        <li><p>Log capture: MobiusHub + PayloadService logs; Client screenshots at key events</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Measurements &amp; Tolerances</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>M1: Obstacle placement: 1.10 m from mower body reference (± 0.01 m)</p></li>
        <li><p>M2: Stop latency: time from first “hazard boundary breach” event to wheel torque =3D 0 or ActivityState =3D EStopped (≤ 2.0 s)</p></li>
        <li><p>M3: Beacon + audible assertion: both active within 0.5 s of e-stop (≤ 0.5 s)</p></li>
        <li><p>M4: Residual motion: vehicle coasts ≤ 0.25 m after stop command</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Test Procedure (Manual Steps)</strong></p>
       <ol>
        <li><p>Verify Preconditions: modes, versions, comms, GNSS, SOC.</p></li>
        <li><p>Place obstacle OB-HZ-01 at 1.10 m from mower body reference point (front bumper datum); record M1.</p></li>
        <li><p>Arm autonomy and start the plan HZ_Breach_Straight_10m.plan.</p></li>
        <li><p>Allow mower to approach; at 2.5–3.0 m before boundary, confirm steady speed (e.g., 0.8–1.2 m/s).</p></li>
        <li><p>Gently slide obstacle 5–10 cm inward to cross the 1.1 m boundary (breach).</p></li>
        <li><p>Record exact time of breach (video + observer callout).</p></li>
        <li><p>Observe for immediate deceleration; verify ActivityState transitions to&nbsp;<strong>EStopped</strong>&nbsp;and StopCategory =3D&nbsp;<strong>Cat0</strong>; record M2/M3/M4.</p></li>
        <li><p>Capture telemetry/logs/screenshots.</p></li>
        <li><p>Remove obstacle, clear e-stop per SOP, verify system healthy.</p></li>
        <li><p>Repeat with second obstacle OB-HZ-02 on rear body reference to validate consistency (optional repeatability pass).</p></li>
       </ol> <p><strong>Expected Behavior (Given/When/Then)</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p><strong>Given</strong>&nbsp;mower in Autonomous mode on the specified plan and environment meets bounds</p></li>
        <li><p><strong>When</strong>&nbsp;an obstacle breaches the 1.1 m hazard boundary</p></li>
        <li><p><strong>Then</strong>&nbsp;mower performs a&nbsp;<strong>Category 0 e-stop</strong>&nbsp;within ≤ 2.0 s, beacon and audible alarm assert, ActivityState =3D EStopped, residual motion ≤ 0.25 m</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Pass/Fail Criteria</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p><strong>Pass:</strong>&nbsp;All of M1–M4 within tolerance; logs show StopCategory =3D Cat0 and ActivityState =3D EStopped.</p></li>
        <li><p><strong>Fail:</strong>&nbsp;Any measurement out of tolerance; stop type ≠ Cat0; state ≠ EStopped; alarms not asserted.</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Attachments &amp; Evidence Required</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>telemetry_&lt;date&gt;_&lt;unit&gt;_HZ110.csv</p></li>
        <li><p>video_side_&lt;date&gt;_HZ110.mp4</p></li>
        <li><p>client_screenshot_&lt;timestamp&gt;.png</p></li>
        <li><p>Distance placement photo with tape/laser visible</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Postconditions / Reset</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>Clear e-stop; verify alarms off; remove obstacles; restore map defaults; archive logs to test run folder.</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Risk Analysis &amp; Mitigations</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>People: risk of contact—<strong>Mitigation:</strong>&nbsp;clear test area; 1 safety spotter; PPE (hi-vis, boots); emergency e-stop reachable.</p></li>
        <li><p>Equipment (mower/obstacle): collision risk—<strong>Mitigation:</strong>&nbsp;foam obstacle; low approach speed; clear escape path.</p></li>
        <li><p>Environment: surface hazards—<strong>Mitigation:</strong>&nbsp;level dry pad only; no bystanders.</p></li>
        <li><p>Communications/GNSS loss—<strong>Mitigation:</strong>&nbsp;pre-check health; abort if degraded.</p></li>
       </ul> <p>Please indicate all the risks associated with running this test case.</p> <p>Risk table should include:</p>
       <ol>
        <li>Damage to the obstacle</li>
        <li>Damage to the mower</li>
        <li>Damage to persons</li>
       </ol>
       <table border=3D"1" cellpadding=3D"1" cellspacing=3D"0">
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td>Risk(s)</td>
          <td>Mitigation(s)</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><p>Damage to the obstacle</p></td>
          <td>Tester uses an obstacle that is expendable</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td>Damage to the mower</td>
          <td>Tester uses an obstacle that will not damage the mower</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td>Damage to persons</td>
          <td>Tester ensures people are outside of the autonomous operating&nbsp;area of the mower&nbsp;</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table> <p><strong>Versioning &amp; Approvals</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>Author: M. Wardrop | Reviewer: V&amp;V Lead | Approver: Safety Mgr</p></li>
        <li><p>Doc ID: TC-HZ-110-v1.2 | Date: 2025-08-26 | Env ID: PRE-PAD-A</p></li>
       </ul> <p><strong>Automation Mapping (optional)</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li><p>Tags: @safety @hazardZone @cat0</p></li>
        <li><p>Step defs: Safety/HazardZone/TC_HZ_110.steps.cs</p></li>
        <li><p>Test runner path: tests/safety/hazard_zone/TC_HZ_110.cs</p></li>
       </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p><strong style=3D"font-style:normal">Preconditions:</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li>&lt;<span style=3D"color:#3498db">Detail the required system state or setup before testing begins.</span>&gt;</li>
       </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Environment:</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li>&lt;<span style=3D"color:#3498db">Include hardware/software configurations, test benches, or simulation tools.</span>&gt;</li>
       </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Equipment:</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li>&lt;<span style=3D"color:#3498db">List all tools, instruments, and simulators used during testing.</span>&gt;</li>
       </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Test Data:</strong></p>
       <ul>
        <li>&lt;<span style=3D"color:#3498db">Provide input data or test conditions required for execution.</span>&gt;</li>
       </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: &lt;table&gt;<br> &lt;tbody&gt;<br>  &lt;tr&gt;<br>   &lt;td&gt;<br>   &lt;p&gt;Set up obstacle within the designated autonomous operating area of the mower&lt;/p&gt;<br>   &lt;/td&gt;<br>  &lt;/tr&gt;<br> &lt;/tbody&gt;<br>&lt;/table&gt;, An obstacle is placed within the autonomous operating area of the mower<br>2: Create a path, or task, that intercepts the obstacle. Assign the mower to the path or task, The mower will be assigned a path or task to intercept the obstacle within the autonomous operating area.<br>3: Ensure the mower is in autonomous mode<br>4: The mower starts the path or task.&amp;nbsp;, &lt;table&gt;<br> &lt;tbody&gt;<br>  &lt;tr&gt;<br>   &lt;td&gt;<br>   &lt;p&gt;As the mower approaches the obstacle, once the mower passes the 3 meter mark away from the obstacle, the mower will slow down&lt;/p&gt;<br>   &lt;/td&gt;<br>  &lt;/tr&gt;<br> &lt;/tbody&gt;<br>&lt;/table&gt;<br>5: The mower approaches the obstacle, As the mower approaches the obstacle, once the mower hits the 1.1 meter mark away from the obstacle, the mower will stop at 1.1 meters.<br>6: The mower is at 1.1 meters from the obstacle.&amp;nbsp;Use the second obstacle to trip the 1.1 meter hazard zone, The mower will immediately category 0 e-stop once the hazard zone has been tripped</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Not Scheduled</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
