   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-61 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213341"> VCU: Autonomous operation halted when perception system is obscured or ineffective </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:55 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">02/01/2026 01:45:28 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-61</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371336</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Autonomous operation halted when perception system is obscured or ineffective</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that if the perception (Obstacle Detection) system becomes ineffective due to environmental conditions, obscurants, faults, or errors, the VCU halts autonomous operation and does not allow the vehicle to continue until the issue is resolved and locally confirmed.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU and Mobius when the perception system is degraded or blinded.<br> • Validation that autonomous mode is immediately halted when sensors become obscured (e.g., LiDAR covered, rain, environmental obscurants).<br> • Validation that clearing the obscurant followed by local confirmation restores the ability to operate autonomously.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-vehicle scenarios where OD/perception system integrity is required for autonomy.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support real-time perception health monitoring.<br> • Ouster Dome LiDAR (or equivalent perception hardware) is active and reporting health status to VAI and Mobius.<br> • Autonomous operation is already permitted and functional prior to inducing the obscured condition.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p>Preconditions:<br> • Vehicle (mower or simulator) is checked into Mobius, powered on, and capable of entering autonomous mode.<br> • Autonomous mode is fully functional with no active perception faults.<br> • Obstacle Detection / Perception system is enabled and reporting valid, healthy data.</p> <p>• Map is published</p> <p>• Waypoint is assigned</p> <p>• Mower is started on the waypoint assignment</p> <p><br> Environment:<br> • Mobius connected and actively monitoring perception sensor status.<br> • Test area free of obstacles so that the perception system is expected to report "clear" before obscurant introduction.<br> • Audio/visual systems enabled for reporting stopped or fault states (if applicable).<br> <br> Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower supporting perception health checks.<br> • Functional perception system (Ouster Dome LiDAR or equivalent).<br> • Tools or materials for temporary obscuring (hand, bag, tape, etc.).<br> <br> Test Data:<br> • Normal perception data (baseline state).<br> • Induced sensor-obscured condition.<br> • Expected results:<br> • Autonomous operation halts with perception-related fault.<br> • After the sensor is uncovered and local confirmation is completed, autonomous operation is allowed again.</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Set holocom value to&amp;nbsp;"sim.VaiSim.ZOcclusion.PosX", 1, Error code is active&amp;nbsp;0xC71C&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Activity State is EStopped&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Mile per hour is 0<br>2: Set holocom value to&amp;nbsp;"sim.VaiSim.ZOcclusion.PosX", 0&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Clear Local Confirmation&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Power engine on&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Begin Mower on waypoint drive&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Check Activity State, Error code&amp;nbsp;0xC71C is not active&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Activity state is Driving</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1557</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-62 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213342"> VCU: VCU asserts E-Stop level error after exceeding idle timeout (5 minutes) -Only asserting 30 seconds- </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:55 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/05/2026 07:03:41 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-62</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371337</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: VCU asserts E-Stop level error after exceeding idle timeout (5 minutes) -Only asserting 30 seconds-</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when the vehicle remains idle beyond the configured idle-timeout duration (IdleMonitor.vehicleIdleTimeoutMsec), the VCU asserts an E-Stop Level Error and requires restart before autonomous operation can resume.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU's idle monitoring logic when the vehicle is not in motion or active for a defined period.<br> • Validation that the idle timeout triggers an E-Stop level error and that the error persists until cleared through restart procedures.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-vehicle environments that support configurable idle-time monitoring.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support the IdleMonitor.vehicleIdleTimeoutMsec DKS configuration.<br> • No active or uncleared errors are present prior to the test, ensuring idle timeout is the sole trigger.<br> • Vehicle is capable of receiving a mission, completing it, and transitioning into an idle state.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p>Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Client and Mobius Server installed, connected, and running.<br> • Vehicle is checked in and able to execute missions.<br> • Vehicle will enter an idle state after mission completion or pause.<br> • No uncleared errors present in Mobius notifications.</p> <p>• Safe Start up has been ran<br> <br> Environment:<br> • Vehicle connected to Mobius with valid communication for DKS configuration and status monitoring.<br> • IdleMonitor.vehicleIdleTimeoutMsec configured to the desired timeout value (example: 30,000 ms =3D 30 seconds).<br> • Environment supports audible/visual reporting of E-Stop level errors (if applicable).<br> <br> Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower supporting idle-time monitoring.<br> • One mower or simulator capable of receiving and executing missions.<br> <br> Test Data:<br> • Configured idle-time threshold value (30 seconds (For now) or 5 minutes) (Later).<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Vehicle enters idle state after mission completion or pause.<br> • VCU asserts E-Stop Level Error when idle time exceeds the configured threshold.<br> • Restart or error-clearing action required before operation resumes.</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: SetDksValue("IdleMonitor.vehicleIdleTimeoutMsec", 30000), Idle Monitor time out is set to 30 seconds<br>2: Create new plan and assign, Plan is created and assigned to the mower<br>3: Play and Pause the Mower for 45 seconds from run operations, Expect Estopped State after the 30 seconds at 45 seconds</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Failed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1680</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-63 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213343"> Mobius: Planner: Disengage Shapes lift and lower reels based on shape perimeter </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:55 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/09/2026 03:03:40 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-63</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371338</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner: Disengage Shapes lift and lower reels based on shape perimeter</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when a disengage shape is present within an area-coverage plan, the VCU and Mobius Planner correctly lift the reels before entering the disengage shape and lower the reels after exiting, based on the shape's perimeter.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the Mobius Planner and VCU when evaluating disengage shapes during plan execution.<br> • Validation that the proximity monitor detects entry into and exit from the disengage shape perimeter and commands reel lift/lower accordingly.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and Simulator-based testing environments supporting disengage-shape logic.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support disengage shape evaluation via the proximity monitor.<br> • Reels and implement systems are functional and can respond to lift/lower commands during plan execution.<br> • Disengage shape is properly drawn and included in the published plan.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p>Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client installed and running.<br> • Mower or simulator checked into Mobius and powered on.<br> • Disengage shape drawn in the testing area, and plan created containing the disengage shape</p> <p>• Safe Start up has been ran</p> <p><br> Environment:<br> • Map published in Mobius with an area-coverage plan that includes a valid disengage shape.<br> • Proximity monitor enabled and evaluating disengage-shape boundaries.<br> • Latest planning libraries installed.<br> <br> Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or Simulator build supporting reel control and disengage-shape logic.<br> • One mower or simulator with a mowing implement capable of reel lift and lower actions.<br> <br> Test Data:<br> • Plan containing a disengage shape.<br> • Expected reel behavior:<br> • Reels raise before entering the disengage shape.<br> • Reels lower after exiting the disengage shape, and mowing resumes.</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create a new plan and assign, New Plan created and assigned<br>2: Begin running the plan into the&amp;nbsp;Disengaged shape, Mower starts running and drives into the&amp;nbsp;Disengaged shape&lt;br /&gt;<br>First PTO Value at 1&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;First Deck Value at 1&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Second Deck Value at 0&amp;nbsp;<br>3: After the mower passes the&amp;nbsp;Disengaged shape and is clear, Deck value is now at 1&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;PTO Value is now at 1</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1708</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-64 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213344"> Mobius: Planner: Reels lift and lower for every action point, even when action points are very close together </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:55 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/12/2026 12:49:32 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-64</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371339</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner: Reels lift and lower for every action point, even when action points are very close together</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the mower correctly lifts and lowers the reels for every action point, regardless of how closely action points are placed, and that no action point commands are skipped or ignored during plan execution.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of Mobius Planner and the VCU when executing area-coverage plans with tightly clustered action points.<br> • Validation that the mower executes all reel-lift and reel-lower commands associated with each action point, even when spacing between action points is minimal.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and Simulator-based environments supporting action-point execution logic.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support reliable action-point command execution and reel-state transitions.<br> • Action points placed close together do not cause command suppression, ignoring, or command overwriting by the implement subsystem.<br> • The mower or simulator is equipped with an implement capable of fast and repeatable reel lift/lower operations.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Area-coverage plan created with action points placed very close together.<br> • Mower or simulator is checked into Mobius and ready to execute the plan.<br> • Implement is attached and capable of reel lift/lower operations.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Map containing area-coverage plan with densely spaced action points is loaded and published in Mobius.<br> • Planning and implement control libraries are up to date.<br> • Proximity monitor and action-point execution logic enabled.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or Simulator build supporting rapid reel state transitions.<br> • One mower or simulator with an attached implement capable of reel lift/lower actions.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Area-coverage plan with tightly spaced action points.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Reels lift and lower for every action point.<br> • No action point commands are missed, skipped, or ignored-even when spacing is minimal.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create a new Plan&amp;nbsp;, Plan is created<br>2: Assign new plan to Mower, Plan is assigned to mower<br>3: Start mower on plan execution, Deck and Reel states change as expected passing over action points:&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;SbrMowerDeckDownDist&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;SbrMowerDeckValue, 1&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;SbrMowerDeckValue, 0&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;SbrMowerDeckDownDist&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;SbrMowerDeckValue, 1&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;SbrMowerDeckValue, 0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Failed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1779</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-65 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213345"> Mobius: Planner: Mowing clean-up path generated around internal no-go zone in the fairway. </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:55 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">02/13/2026 12:55:41 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-65</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371340</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner: Mowing clean-up path generated around internal no-go zone in the fairway.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the Mobius Server and Area Coverage Planner generate a mowing clean-up path (headland lap) around internal obstacles (no-go zones) within a fairway area-coverage map so that the mower can mow around the internal obstacle.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the Area Coverage Planner when processing internal obstacles such as lakes, bunkers, or permanent no-go zones inside an area-coverage region.<br> • Validation that the planner identifies internal obstacles and generates headland laps around them rather than planning through the obstacle.<br> • Validation that the resulting plan allows the mower to physically mow around the obstacle perimeter.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and Simulator environments supporting internal obstacle handling.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support internal-obstacle identification and clean-up path generation.<br> • Internal no-go zones are drawn, tagged, or provided in a manner recognized by the planner.<br> • Obstacles meet minimum drivable-radius constraints for producing a valid headland lap.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client installed, running, and configured with the internal-obstacle feature enabled.<br> • Area-coverage map created and published with at least one internal obstacle ( lake, bunker, object ).<br> • Vehicle (mower or simulator) checked in and available for planning operations.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Map loaded in Mobius with internal no-go zone fully enclosed within the fairway boundaries.<br> • Area Coverage Planner configured to generate headland laps for internal obstacles.<br> • Planning libraries updated to the latest version.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or Simulator build supporting internal-obstacle clean-up path generation.<br> • One mower or simulator capable of executing headland laps around an internal obstacle.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Area-coverage plan containing internal obstacle(s).<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Planner generates a clean-up path (headland lap) fully around the internal obstacle.<br> • Mower can mow around the obstacle without missing the perimeter or crossing into the no-go zone.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create, Assign Offline plan with no-go zone(s), Plan is created and assigned<br>2: Wait for plan assignment, Expect no-go zones are not breached&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Verify&amp;nbsp;segments don't intersect with rough shapes inside the fairway</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1790</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-66 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213346"> Mobius: Path Builder: User-added action points lift and lower reels </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:55 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/10/2026 10:55:10 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-66</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371341</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Path Builder: User-added action points lift and lower reels</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that Mobius allows the user to add action points within Path Builder that command the mower to lift and lower the reels, and that these user-defined action points are executed correctly by the vehicle.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of Mobius Path Builder when users place action points that trigger implement actions.<br> • Validation that user-added action points correctly map to reel lift and reel lower actions in the executed path.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and Simulator-based environments supporting Path Builder functionality.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support reel lift/lower actions via user-defined Path Builder action points.<br> • The implement supports commandable reel operations through action points.<br> • Telemetry relevant to deck and implement operations (e.g., "Deck" telemetry) is enabled and visible in Mobius.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p>Preconditions:<br> • User is in Mobius with Path Builder available.<br> • A path has been created but not yet selected in Path Builder mode (per the system precondition).<br> • Mower or simulator is checked into Mobius and capable of executing implement commands.<br> • Telemetry configuration updated to include deck-related telemetry (e.g., "Deck" signals enabled under Global Telemetry).</p> <p>• Mower is checked into mobius and ready to receive assignment of a plan.</p> <p>• Plan with user added Action Points, already created and ready to be assigned<br> <br> Environment:<br> • Path Builder mode active in Mobius.<br> • Path configured to accept user-added action points.<br> • Planning libraries and telemetry subscriptions up to date.<br> <br> Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or Simulator build supporting user-defined implement actions.<br> • One mower or simulator with an attached implement capable of reel lift/lower operations.<br> <br> Test Data:<br> • Path Builder path containing user-added action points.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Vehicle executes lift and lower reel actions in the order defined by the user.<br> • Action points configured in Path Builder appear in the executed path and are not skipped.</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Assign User Added Action Points Plan&amp;nbsp; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; Run, Expected Deck actions happen&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;DeckLift, 1 //Action Point DeckLift: ON&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;DeckLower, 1 //Action Point DeckLower: ON&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;DeckLift, 0 //Action Point DeckLift: OFF&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;DeckLower, 0 //Action Point DeckLower: OFF&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;SbrMowerDeckValue, 1 //Action Point CMD: Deck Down<br>2: Run plan again, Expected Deck actions happen&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;SbrMowerDeckValue, 0 //Action Point CMD: Deck Up&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;SbrMowerDeckValue, 1 //Action Point CMD: Deck Dn Dist<br>3: Run plan again, Expected Deck actions happen&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;SbrMowerDeckValue, 0 &amp;nbsp;//Action Point CMD: Deck Up</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1801</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-67 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213347"> VCU: System triggers E-Stop when an obstacle is detected in the Hazard zone </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:55 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/09/2026 02:07:53 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-67</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371342</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: System triggers E-Stop when an obstacle is detected in the Hazard zone</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when an obstacle is detected inside the yield zone, the system immediately triggers a Hazard Zone response resulting in an E-Stop, and that the yield-zone timeout parameter (ODZones.yieldZoneTimeoutMsec) behaves correctly, including default value, configurability, and persistence.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU and Mobius safety system when an obstacle enters the yield zone.<br> • Validation that with the yield-zone timeout set to 0 ms, any obstacle in the yield zone immediately escalates to a hazard condition and triggers an E-Stop.<br> • Validation that the yield-zone timeout parameter:<br> • Has a default value of 0 ms,<br> • Can be modified by the user through DKS,<br> • Persists across vehicle restart.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-vehicle testing environments.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support yield-zone detection and timeout configuration.<br> • The obstacle detection system is active and correctly reporting yield-zone occupancy.<br> • DKS is accessible and allows setting and persisting ODZones.yieldZoneTimeoutMsec.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p>Preconditions:<br> • Obstacle present or introduced into the yield zone.<br> • Default value for yield-zone timeout is 0 ms unless modified via DKS.<br> • Vehicle or simulator checked into Mobius and operational.<br> • No uncleared errors present prior to initiating the test.</p> <p>• Need an obstacle to be in the Hazard zone to trigger expected states</p> <p>• Mower is ready to run and accept assignment of a waypoint to drive</p> <p><br> <br> Environment:<br> • Mobius connected to the vehicle with valid communication for DKS parameter changes.<br> • DKS page accessible to read and modify ODZones.yieldZoneTimeoutMsec.<br> • Restart behavior available to validate persistence of yield-zone timeout values.<br> • Obstacle detection zones (yield/hazard) configured and active.<br> <br> Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower with working OD system.<br> • One mower or simulator capable of reporting yield-zone occupancy and triggering E-Stop conditions.<br> • Holocom to access to VCU DKS interface.<br> <br> Test Data:<br> • Yield-zone timeout parameter:<br> • Default: 0 ms<br> • User-modified value via DKS<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Obstacle in Yield Zone → Immediate Hazard Zone escalation → E-Stop triggered<br> • User can modify yield-zone timeout in DKS<br> • Modified value persists after restart</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Mower is assigned a waypoint and started on a waypoint drive, Mower is running the waypoint with a min velocity of .5<br>2: Trigger Obstacle in Hazard Zone - Currently using an obstacle shape drawn on a map and then published, Currently verifies that a conditional e-stop fault is set and velocity is zero&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;**Needs to be triggered with a better obstacle - going to look into teleporting another mower.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1802</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-68 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213348"> Mobius: Verify vehicle behavior when associated client disconnects from server </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:55 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">02/13/2026 12:51:41 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-68</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371343</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Verify vehicle behavior when associated client disconnects from server</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify the system behavior when the client associated with the operator user disconnects from Mobius Server, specifically ensuring that the vehicle behaves according to the updated system logic (vehicle continues operation when the operator's client disconnects).<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of Mobius Server when a vehicle is assigned to a user account and that user's associated client disconnects.<br> • Validation of both:<br> • Legacy behavior (vehicle pauses when the controlling user disconnects), and<br> • Updated system behavior (vehicle continues mowing after operator device disconnects, and Mobius updates mowing status when the user reconnects).<br> • Includes assignment of missions, client login/disconnection, and verification of vehicle status from secondary user accounts.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-vehicle environments connected to Mobius Server.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support updated disconnect-handling behavior (Nov 9, 2023 update).<br> • Multiple user accounts exist within the system and can be logged in simultaneously on separate devices.<br> • The vehicle is assigned to one operator account and can execute missions during the test.<br> • Network disconnects or logout events are properly detected by Mobius Server.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p>Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Mobius Client installed, configured, and running.<br> • At least two user accounts are available with unique login credentials.<br> • A vehicle (mower or simulator) is checked into Mobius and ready for mission assignment.<br> • Vehicle can execute a mission (path or area-coverage) under the control of the assigned operator user.</p> <p>• A role is created and can be assigned</p> <p>• Two users are created to run the test with</p> <p>• Map is loaded and ready for use</p> <p><br> <br> Environment:<br> • Multiple Mobius client sessions available (desktop, mobile, or simulator clients).<br> • Reliable network connectivity for login/logout and disconnect testing.<br> • Mission assignment enabled and verified operational for the vehicle.<br> • Updated disconnect behavior enabled (vehicle continues mowing when operator client disconnects).<br> <br> Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower capable of mission execution.<br> • Two devices or simulated clients for two independent user sessions.<br> • Mobius Server environment capable of tracking real-time client connections/disconnections.<br> <br> Test Data:<br> • Two user accounts with different credentials.<br> • Vehicle assigned to one user.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Vehicle continues autonomous operation when the assigned operator's client disconnects (Nov 9 update).<br> • Reconnecting user sees updated vehicle location and mowing status.<br> • System accurately reflects vehicle as active, not paused, after operator disconnect.</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Assign mower to User u&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Switch to User u, User U is assigned the mower<br>2: Create a plan and assign to the mower, Plan is created and assigned<br>3: Start the mower on the assigned plan, Mower is running the plan<br>4: Switch Hubs to User u&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Switch Hubs to User u2&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;**Simulates User (Client) is disconnected&lt;br /&gt;<br>Overserve transition of activity state from Driving to Inactive&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;-Clear Assignments&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;-Clear EStops, ActivityState&amp;nbsp;Inactive&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;ActivityState&amp;nbsp;EStopped&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;<br>5: Assign asset to User2&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Start Mower on the mission&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Switch Hub to User U, Mower is driving after resume</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Failed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1806</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-69 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213349"> VCU: Verify operational sequences for pausing, estopping, resuming, finishing, and starting mowing is followed </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:55 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/11/2026 01:27:13 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-69</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371344</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Verify operational sequences for pausing, estopping, resuming, finishing, and starting mowing is followed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the VCU and Mobius system follow the required operational sequences for:<br> • Pausing mowing<br> • E-Stopping<br> • Resuming mowing<br> • Finishing a plan<br> • Starting a plan<br> • Ensure each sequence is executed in the correct order and that all transitions (vehicle motion, PTO state, park brake, reels, engine state, direction changes) are properly logged in Mobius.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU when transitioning between mowing states that require specific mechanical and motion sequences.<br> • Validation of sequence order for:<br> • Pause sequence: Stop vehicle → PTO off → Park brake on<br> • E-Stop sequence: Stop vehicle → Park brake on → PTO off → Engine off<br> • Resume sequence: PTO on → Reels up (Crosscut) → Park brake off → Reverse → Forward → Reels down<br> • Finish sequence: Motion stopped → Park brake on → PTO off → Reels lifted (Transport)<br> • Start sequence: PTO on → Park brake off → Forward motion → Reels down<br> • Verifies that each sequence is both executed correctly and logged correctly in Mobius Server and data systems.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-vehicle test environments.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support state transitions and logging for all required operational sequences.<br> • Vehicle implement systems (PTO, reels) and motion systems (forward, reverse, braking) are functioning and report accurate telemetry.<br> • System logging is enabled such that sequence order can be verified via database data, telemetry logs, or Mobius visualization.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p>Preconditions:<br> • Vehicle is currently mowing in an active mission.<br> • System has detected or will simulate a condition that requires mowing to be paused, estopped, resumed, finished, or started.<br> • Vehicle checked into Mobius, powered on, and capable of executing implement and motion transitions.<br> • Test setup includes ability to capture logs (per AG-1805 or similar).</p> <p>• Plan created and ready for assignment</p> <p>• Pan assigned to mower, and mower ready to run</p> <p><br> Environment:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running and connected to the vehicle.<br> • Logging systems (database, telemetry, event logs) operational and capturing the sequence transitions.<br> • Environment supports real-time observation or log-based verification (visual or data-driven).<br> • Implement and drive subsystems active and responsive.<br> <br> Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower capable of executing and reporting all operational sequences.<br> • One mower or simulator with functional implement (PTO, reels) and braking systems.<br> <br> Test Data:<br> • Required sequence definitions:<br> • Pause: Stop motion → PTO off → Park brake on<br> • E-Stop: Stop motion → Park brake on → PTO off → Engine off<br> • Resume: PTO on → Reels up (Crosscut) → Park brake off → Reverse → Forward → Reels down<br> • Finish Plan: Motion stopped → Park brake on → PTO off → Reels to Transport<br> • Start Plan: PTO on → Park brake off → Forward motion → Reels down<br> <br> • Expected behavior:<br> • All sequences are executed correctly and in order.<br> • All sequence steps are present in logs and/or visually confirmed.</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: &lt;p&gt;**Begin running mower on assigned plan&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Pause operations - expected states&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;ol&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;Verify that the vehicle motion is stopped.&lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;Verify that the PTO is turned off.&lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;Verify that the park brake is on.&lt;/li&gt;<br>&lt;/ol&gt;, **Current verification order - needs to be updated&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;parkingBrakeOnTime &amp;gt; zeroVelocityTime &amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;br /&gt;<br>ptoOffTime &amp;gt; zeroVelocityTime&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;This verifies:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Both&lt;/strong&gt; “park brake ON” and “PTO OFF” happen &lt;strong&gt;after&lt;/strong&gt; “velocity zero”<br>2: &lt;p&gt;**Begin running mower on assigned plan - after objective is cleared, estops cleared, and a new plan is assigned&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;E-Stopping Sequence - expected states Trigger by setting the DKS value ("SafetyTest.Test Estop Soft", 1)&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;ol&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;Verify that the vehicle motion is stopped.&lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;Verify that the Park brake is on&lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;Verify that the PTO is turned off.&lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;Verify that the Engine is off&lt;/li&gt;<br>&lt;/ol&gt;, **Current verification order - needs to be updated&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;parkingBrakeOnTime &amp;gt; zeroVelocityTime &amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;br /&gt;<br>ptoOffTime &amp;gt; zeroVelocityTime &amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;br /&gt;<br>engineOffTime &amp;gt; zeroVelocityTime;&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;This verifies:&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Park brake ON happens &lt;strong&gt;after&lt;/strong&gt; velocity is zero&lt;br /&gt;<br>PTO OFF happens &lt;strong&gt;after&lt;/strong&gt; velocity is zero&lt;br /&gt;<br>Engine OFF happens &lt;strong&gt;after&lt;/strong&gt; velocity is zero<br>3: &lt;p&gt;Resuming Operations - Expected states&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;ol&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify PTO on&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify Reels up (Crosscut)&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify Park brake off&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify Reverse&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify Forward&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify reels down&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br>&lt;/ol&gt;, **Current verification order - needs to be updated - missing&amp;nbsp;SbrMowerReelsValue proper placement and&amp;nbsp;SbrMowerReelsValue&amp;nbsp;down.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;<br>ptoOnTime &amp;lt; reverseVelocityTime&lt;br /&gt;<br>&amp;amp;&amp;amp; parkingBrakeOnTime &amp;lt; reverseVelocityTime&lt;br /&gt;<br>&amp;amp;&amp;amp; reverseVelocityTime &amp;lt; forwardVelocityTime;&lt;br /&gt;<br>&lt;br /&gt;<br>&lt;br /&gt;<br>PTO ON happens &lt;strong&gt;before&lt;/strong&gt; reverse starts&lt;br /&gt;<br>Parking brake &lt;em&gt;ON&lt;/em&gt; happens &lt;strong&gt;before&lt;/strong&gt; reverse starts&lt;br /&gt;<br>Reverse starts &lt;strong&gt;before&lt;/strong&gt; forward starts<br>4: &lt;p&gt;**Begin running mower on assigned plan - after objective is cleared, estops cleared, and a new plan is assigned&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Finishing a plan (Exclude Pause)&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;ol&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify Motion stopped&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify Park Brake is on&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify PTO is off&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify the Reels are lifted in to (Transport)&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br>&lt;/ol&gt;, **Current verification order - needs to be updated - Missing Parking Brake Off and Reels lifted states.&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;ptoOnTime &amp;lt; forwardVelocityTime &amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;br /&gt;<br>parkingBrakeOnTime &amp;lt; forwardVelocityTime;&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;This verifies: &lt;strong&gt;PTO ON&lt;/strong&gt; happens &lt;strong&gt;before&lt;/strong&gt; forward motion starts, and &lt;strong&gt;Park Brake ON&lt;/strong&gt; happens &lt;strong&gt;before&lt;/strong&gt; forward motion starts.<br>5: &lt;p&gt;**Begin running mower on assigned plan - after objective is cleared, estops cleared, and a new plan is assigned&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Starting a plan (Exclude Pause)&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;ol&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify the PTO on&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify the Park brake off&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify Forward Motion is started&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Verify Reels are down&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br>&lt;/ol&gt;, &lt;p&gt;**Current verification order - needs to be updated - Missing:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;ul&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;PTO on (code checks PTO &lt;strong&gt;off&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Park brake off&amp;nbsp;(code checks brake &lt;strong&gt;on&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Forward motion started (not checked)&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;Reels down (code checks &lt;strong&gt;transport mode&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br>&lt;/ul&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;parkingBrakeOnTime &amp;gt; zeroVelocityTime &amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;br /&gt;<br>ptoOffTime &amp;gt; zeroVelocityTime &amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;br /&gt;<br>reelsTransportModeTime &amp;gt; zeroVelocityTime;&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;This verifies: &lt;strong&gt;after motion reaches “stopped” (velocity zero)&lt;/strong&gt;, you observe:&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;ul&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parking brake ON&lt;/strong&gt; (not off)&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PTO OFF&lt;/strong&gt; (not on)&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br> &lt;li&gt;<br> &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reels in “Transport mode”&lt;/strong&gt; (which usually implies reels &lt;strong&gt;up&lt;/strong&gt;, not down)&lt;/p&gt;<br> &lt;/li&gt;<br>&lt;/ul&gt;</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Failed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1807</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-70 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213350"> VCU: Verify E-Stop when 4G/LTE signal is lost </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:55 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/09/2026 03:01:39 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-70</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371345</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Verify E-Stop when 4G/LTE signal is lost</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when the vehicle loses its 4G/LTE network connection while in motion, the VCU initiates an E-Stop and brings the vehicle to a complete stop, and that the loss-of-signal condition is correctly logged by the system.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU and Mobius system when the primary cellular communication link is interrupted.<br> • Validation that the loss of 4G/LTE connectivity results in an immediate E-Stop condition.<br> • Validation that the system logs clearly indicate the E-Stop was triggered due to cellular-signal loss.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-vehicle environments where 4G/LTE connectivity is present.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support E-Stop initiation upon loss of 4G/LTE communication.<br> • The vehicle is capable of detecting cellular-signal loss and reporting that condition through available telemetry/logging.<br> • 4G/LTE disruption can be simulated via signal blocker, antenna disabling, or turning off the source.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p>Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Client and Mobius Server are installed, running, and communicating with the vehicle.<br> • Vehicle is connected to the 4G/LTE network and currently in motion under a mission.<br> • No uncleared safety or operational errors prior to triggering the test.</p> <p>• Mower is ready to run an assigned plan.<br> <br> Environment:<br> • Network environment where 4G/LTE connectivity can be disrupted on demand.<br> • Mission assigned and vehicle actively executing the mission.<br> • System logging enabled for communication status and E-Stop events.<br> <br> Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower with working 4G/LTE communication.<br> • Means to interrupt cellular signal (signal blocker, disabling network source, hardware power-off, etc.).<br> • A mower or simulator capable of responding to E-Stop commands.<br> <br> Test Data:<br> • Active mission with the vehicle in motion.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Loss of 4G/LTE connectivity triggers E-Stop.<br> • Vehicle comes to a complete stop.<br> • Logs indicate E-Stop was due to signal loss.</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create, Assign plan &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Begin Plan execution &amp;gt;&amp;gt;, Mower is running the assigned plan and gets to a velocity greater than 0<br>2: Disrupt 4G/LTE Signal with&amp;nbsp;DeleteServerListeningPort(14000), Expect:&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Simulator checked out&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Estop 0x0503 fault state</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1808</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-71 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213351"> VCU: Verify maximum mowing speed of 6 MPH on straights </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/09/2026 02:59:55 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-71</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371346</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Verify maximum mowing speed of 6 MPH on straights</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the mower maintains a maximum mowing speed of 6 MPH while traveling on straight segments of an area-coverage plan and that the reels remain engaged and operating during mowing.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU when executing straight-line mowing segments under a configured maximum mowing speed.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Map speed ≥ 6 MPH<br> • Implement (mowing) speed =3D 6 MPH<br> • Vehicle maintains 6 MPH on straight sections<br> • Reels remain engaged and functional<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-mower test environments supporting speed-controlled mowing.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support 6 MPH mowing speed limits.<br> • Mower implement is correctly configured for mowing operations at 6 MPH.<br> • Straight segments of the area-coverage plan allow the mower to achieve and maintain 6 MPH without turning limitations.<br> • Map speed and implement speed settings override lower default speeds when allowed.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p>Preconditions:<br> • Mowing equipment installed, configured, and functional.<br> • Mower is positioned on a straight surface suitable for verifying top mowing speed.<br> • Map speed is set to 6 MPH or above.<br> • Implement speed is set to 6 MPH.<br> • Vehicle checked into Mobius and ready to execute area-coverage operations.</p> <p>• Implement speed with is set DksSetting("Pace.throttlePID.Kp", 6.5),&nbsp;DksSetting("Pace.throttlePID.Ki", 2.25)<br> <br> Environment:<br> • Area-coverage plan with straight segments loaded and published in Mobius.<br> • Speed gauges and telemetry visible in Mobius Client for real-time monitoring.<br> • Reels fully operational and configured for mowing engagement.<br> <br> Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower capable of mowing at 6 MPH.<br> • One mower or simulator with a functional mowing implement and reel engagement capability.<br> <br> Test Data:<br> • Configured speed data:<br> • Map max speed ≥ 6 MPH<br> • Implement mowing speed =3D 6 MPH<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Vehicle maintains 6 MPH on straight-line mowing.<br> • Reels remain engaged and operating.<br> • Telemetry and gauge readings confirm speed stability at 6 MPH.</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Update Map shape Speed Limit for 16A FW &amp;amp; 16 DR to 6 miles per hour or higher, Map shape(s) speed limit updated to 10 mph<br>2: Create new offline plan with updated map shape speeds&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Assign new plan to mower&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Begin running mower on plan&amp;nbsp;, New plan is create&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;New Plan is assigned&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Mower begins running plan<br>3: Wait for the Mowers Desk Value to be 1 (Down for Mowing), Mower has the deck in position and is mowing<br>4: Wait for mower to reach the desired speed of 6 mph&amp;nbsp;, Verify that the mower reaches a Velocity of 6 mph</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1818</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-72 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213352"> VCU: Verify maximum transport-mode speed of 10 MPH </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/09/2026 01:56:53 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-72</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371347</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Verify maximum transport-mode speed of 10 MPH</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when the mower is operating in transport mode, the VCU limits the vehicle speed to 10 MPH, even when the assigned path or operator settings request a higher speed.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU when executing a Path Builder path in transport mode.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Path or map speed may be set above 10 MPH,<br> • Transport mode speed limiting correctly caps the speed at 10 MPH,<br> • Vehicle telemetry reflects the enforced limit.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-mower environments supporting transport-mode speed governance.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support transport-mode speed limiting to 10 MPH.<br> • The mower implement is raised or in a non-mowing configuration, qualifying the vehicle for transport-mode operation.<br> • Path Builder paths correctly execute at the requested transport speed, subject to VCU speed limits.<br> • The operator can configure map speed and path speed values above and below 10 MPH.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mower is in transport mode (reels raised, implement disengaged).<br> • Path Builder path is created and functional.<br> • Transport-mode speed (path speed) is adjustable and can be set by the operator.<br> • Map speed is set to 10 MPH or above.<br> • Vehicle is checked into Mobius and capable of autonomous transport operation.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Straight or sufficiently long path available for achieving constant-speed transport operation (at least ~100 feet).<br> • Mobius Client configured to display speed telemetry and vehicle gauges.<br> • Planner and VCU libraries updated to the latest version.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower capable of transport-mode operation.<br> • One mower or simulator with transport-mode capability and functioning drive subsystem.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Path with speed set above 10 MPH.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Vehicle maintains 10 MPH or less in transport mode.<br> • Even if path or map requests higher speed, VCU enforces the 10 MPH limit.<br> • Mobius telemetry/gauges confirm speed capping at 10 MPH.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Update Map shape speeds on Hole 16 and FW 16 to 30 Miles Per Hour, Map shape speed updated to 10 mph for both&amp;nbsp;Hole 16 and FW 16 to 30 mph<br>2: Assign a way point with velocity of 10 mph&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Wait for velocity to be greater than 1 mph, Waypoint was assigned&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Velocity reaches 1 mph or higher<br>3: Wait for 1 minute for full velocity to be reached, Verify 10 mph reached in Transport Mode</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1819</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-73 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213353"> VCU: Verify maximum reverse speed of 4 MPH </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">02/21/2026 02:10:30 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-73</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371348</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Verify maximum reverse speed of 4 MPH</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when the mower is operating in reverse under autonomous control, the VCU limits the vehicle speed to 4 MPH or less, regardless of path or operator speed settings.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU when executing a reverse-direction autonomous path.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Reverse motion is permitted,<br> • Reverse-speed limiting is enforced at 4 MPH,<br> • Mobius telemetry correctly reports governed reverse speed.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-vehicle environments supporting reverse autonomous movement.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support reverse-speed limiting.<br> • The mower is capable of autonomous reverse movement.<br> • ODZones.reverseLimitMeters is configured to allow sufficient reverse distance (≥ 50).<br> • Vehicle speed commands higher than 4 MPH in reverse are overridden by the VCU.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"><p>Preconditions:<br> • Mower can drive in reverse while in autonomous mode.<br> • Mobius Server and Mobius Client are installed, running, and connected.<br> • Reverse-limit distance (ODZones.reverseLimitMeters) is set to 50 or above.<br> • Vehicle checked into Mobius and capable of executing a reverse path or waypoint mission.</p> <p><br> Environment:<br> • Reverse path or reverse waypoint created and published.<br> • Sufficient space available for safe reverse testing.<br> • Mobius Client configured to display vehicle speed gauge/telemetry.<br> • Planner and VCU libraries updated to latest version.<br> <br> Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower capable of autonomous reverse motion.<br> • One mower or simulator with drive system supporting controlled reverse speed.<br> <br> Test Data:<br> • Autonomous reverse path or reverse waypoint.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Vehicle moves in reverse direction.<br> • Speed does not exceed 4 MPH.<br> • Mobius telemetry confirms speed limiting at or below 4 MPH.</p></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Assign Waypoint with 10 MPH velocity in reverse&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Begin running the mower on the plan, Waypoint was assigned with velocity&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Mower begins running plan<br>2: Check velocity in reverse, Verify 4 mph isn't breached</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1820</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-74 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213354"> VCU: Variable reverse-warning zone based on machine speed </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/09/2026 02:03:04 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-74</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371349</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Variable reverse-warning zone based on machine speed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the warning zone distance dynamically adjusts based on the mower's reverse speed, and ensure that when the mower approaches an obstacle in reverse, it comes to a controlled stop within the warning zone before entering the hazard zone.<br> • Confirm that increasing reverse speed (2 MPH → 3 MPH → 4 MPH) does not change the expectation that the mower stops within the warning zone and does not trigger hazard-zone violations.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU's reverse-direction obstacle detection system when approaching an obstacle at varying speeds.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Warning zone scales with speed.<br> • Vehicle halts within the warning zone each time.<br> • No hazard-zone violation occurs under expected operating conditions.<br> • Standoff violation warnings appear appropriately.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-vehicle environments using OD-based reverse safety zones.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support variable warning-zone scaling based on reverse speed.<br> • Obstacle detection (yield, warning, hazard) zones are correctly configured and reporting.<br> • Reverse speeds of 2–4 MPH fall within OD system tested parameters.<br> • Map speed and/or Path speed settings override default speed but do not disable safety zone behaviors.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • A physical or simulated obstacle is set up on the track.<br> • The mower is positioned outside of the warning zone prior to each test run.<br> • Operator is able to adjust map/path speed (2 MPH, 3 MPH, 4 MPH).<br> • Vehicle is checked into Mobius and capable of reverse motion under autonomous operation.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Testing area supports safe reverse motion toward a known obstacle.<br> • Mobius connected to the mower for real-time OD zone feedback and standoff violation warnings.<br> • Warning and hazard zone logic active for reverse operation.<br> • Logging enabled for zone transitions (standoff, warning, hazard).<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower with functional OD sensors.<br> • One mower or simulator capable of reverse motion and OD-based stopping.<br> • An obstacle suitable for triggering OD warning zones.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Reverse speeds tested: 2 MPH, 3 MPH, 4 MPH.<br> • Expected behavior for each speed:<br> • Vehicle approaches obstacle in reverse.<br> • Vehicle comes to a complete stop within the warning zone.<br> • Standoff violation warning may appear after ~2 seconds.<br> • No hazard-zone violation occurs.<br> • Increasing speed does not change expected outcomes.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create, Assign Offline plan &amp;gt;&amp;gt; Begin Plan execution in reverse&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Trigger Obstacle in Yield Zone (Yield Zone-No Longer exists), Expect Fault conditions at variable speeds</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1822</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-75 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213355"> VCU: Reels lift to transport when starting new area-coverage plan; no forward motion with reels down unless mowing </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/12/2026 07:44:32 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-75</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371350</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Reels lift to transport when starting new area-coverage plan; no forward motion with reels down unless mowing</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when a new Area Coverage Plan (ACP) is started, the mower automatically lifts the reels to transport mode before driving to the plan's starting point, regardless of whether the previous plan was paused, resumed, cleared, or E-stopped.<br> • Confirm that the vehicle never moves forward with reels down unless it is actively mowing within an ACP.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU and Mobius when transitioning between ACPs and driving toward a new start location.<br><br>Validation that:<br> • Reels are lifted to transport mode when leaving any previously active plan.<br> • Mower drives toward the new ACP start only with reels raised.<br> • Reels remain down only while actively mowing inside the area-coverage region.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-vehicle environments supporting ACP transitions.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support automatic implement transitions during plan changes.<br> • Reels and implement control systems accurately report transport and mowing positions.<br> • System properly clears or transitions between multiple ACPs.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client are installed and running.<br> • Area Coverage Plan (ACP) is available and published.<br> • Mower or simulator is checked in and capable of executing ACPs.<br> • Reels are down and the mower is actively mowing within a plan (initial state for test).<br><br>Environment:<br> • ACP loaded in Mobius, with a designated start point reachable by the vehicle.<br> • Logging enabled for reel position, mission state, and motion state.<br> • Environment allows safe transitions between ACPs and plan restarts.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower with functional reel lift/lower actuation.<br> • One mower or simulator capable of automatically transitioning reels between transport and mowing modes.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Area Coverage Plans used for:<br> • Initial mowing<br> • Clearing / reloading<br> • Starting a new ACP<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Reels lift to transport mode immediately when a new ACP is started.<br> • Mower drives to the new starting point with reels up.<br> • No forward motion occurs with reels down unless the machine is actively mowing.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Start Mower on an Area Coverage Plan, Expect Reels are lifted to transport</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1829</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-76 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213356"> Mobius: Mowing history remains consistent when clean-up lap is executed first (Outside-In) </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/09/2026 01:51:42 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-76</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371351</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Mowing history remains consistent when clean-up lap is executed first (Outside-In)</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when an Area Coverage Plan (ACP) executes the clean-up lap first, the mowing history recorded in Mobius remains accurate and consistent. Specifically, the system must not mark the mowing as 100 percent complete after only the clean-up lap is finished.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of Mobius and the VCU when an ACP is configured to perform the clean-up lap before the interior mowing pattern.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Mowing history is updated incrementally and correctly.<br> • Clean-up laps do not incorrectly set the overall completion percentage to 100 percent.<br> • History displayed in Mobius remains aligned with actual mowing progress.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-vehicle ACP execution environments.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support both clean-up-lap-first (Outside-In) ACPs and mowing-history tracking.<br> • Mowing history represents both perimeter and interior mowing progress as distinct portions of the ACP.<br> • ACP configuration allows clean-up laps to run prior to normal mowing rows.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client are installed, running, and connected.<br> • Area Coverage Plan (ACP) is created and configured to execute the clean-up lap first (Outside-In).<br> • Mower or simulator is checked in and capable of running an ACP with history tracking enabled.<br><br>Environment:<br> • ACP with clean-up-lap-first (Outside-In) logic published in Mobius.<br> • Mowing history visible in Mobius Client (coverage visualization, percentages, or progress data).<br> • Logging enabled to capture mowing-history updates.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or simulator capable of executing clean-up laps and providing accurate mowing-history telemetry.<br> • One mower or simulator with a functional mowing implement.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • ACP configured with:<br> • Clean-up lap first (Outside-In)<br> • Remaining coverage rows following the lap<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Mowing history does not show 100 percent completion after clean-up lap only.<br> • History remains consistent with actual progress.<br> • Coverage visualization reflects only perimeter completion, not total ACP completion.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Load OfflinePlan setting the Boundary Lap Generation order to Cleanup Ordering OutsideIn., Expect that Coverage Percent complete is correct (within tolerence)</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1831</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-77 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213357"> Mobius: Planner generates cleanup laps with square corners </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:29:52 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-77</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371352</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner generates cleanup laps with square corners</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the Mobius Planner correctly generates cleanup laps with square corners when the fairway geometry contains angles between 90° and 120° ± 10°, and that the Planner respects the design rules for handling approaches, allowable turn types, and angle constraints.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the Area Coverage Planner when creating cleanup laps for fairways with square-corner geometry.<br> • Validation that the Planner:<br> • Identifies corners exceeding the threshold angle (default X =3D 45°).<br> • Automatically generates cleanup laps with square corner transitions on approaches.<br> • Minimizes unnecessary turning on the approach.<br> • Uses rough-terrain turning behaviors for tighter corners.<br> • Performs 3-point turns when insufficient space exists for normal turns.<br> • Prioritizes regular turns when space allows.<br> • Handles minimum 90° and maximum 120° corners (±10°).<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real mower planning systems that support cleanup-lap geometry.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU Planner builds support square-corner cleanup logic.<br> • Pushing the reel lift toward the approach is preferred because the approach is cut shorter and allows more tolerance for drop/lift locations.<br> • The fairway or test map contains at least one valid square corner according to planner angle constraints.<br> • Out of scope (not validated in this test):<br> • Square corners not part of the approach<br> • Adding additional cleanup laps<br> • Modifying turns on straight swaths<br> • Altering headland-related turning logic outside the approach</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server installed and running.<br> • Mobius Client running and connected.<br> • SimManager mower Holo file available or real mower connected.<br> • Map or fairway shape created or loaded with at least one square corner (90°–120° ±10°).<br><br>Environment:<br> • Fairway geometry published in Mobius with visible square-corner boundaries.<br> • Planner configured to use default angle threshold (X =3D 45°) for determining when square-corner rules apply.<br> • Planner libraries updated to support cleanup-lap generation and three-point turn logic.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or Simulator supporting cleanup-lap and turn-type planning logic.<br> • One mower or simulator configured for approach, headland, and turn evaluation.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Fairway geometry with corner angles between 90° and 120° (±10°).<br> • Planner-generated cleanup laps.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Cleanup lap includes square-corner transitions where applicable.<br> • Planner does not skip coverage near square corners.<br> • Planner still generates valid plans when angle parameter is changed from Auto.<br> • Planner generates 3-point turns when insufficient space exists.<br> • Planner generates regular turns when space is available.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Load a plan with square corners, Expect that the plan in specific segments has accounted for the square corners</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1874</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-78 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213358"> Mobius: Exported Objective DB table contains valid plan name when resuming a saved plan </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 05:10:10 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-78</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371353</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Exported Objective DB table contains valid plan name when resuming a saved plan</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when a previously exported objective plan is loaded or resumed, the exported objective database table contains a valid and correct plan name, ensuring plan-name consistency across save, export, load, and resume operations.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the Mobius data-export system when saving and loading Area Coverage Plans (ACP).<br> • Validation that:<br> • The plan name is stored correctly during export.<br> • The correct plan name appears in ExportedObjectiveLoaded.csv when the plan is loaded from server or local storage.<br> • No NULL, empty, or mismatched plan names are present.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and Mobius Server environments with objective export functionality.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server and Mobius Client builds support objective export and plan resumption functionality.<br> • Database export location and structure are stable, including expected CSV filenames.<br> • User can save ACPs locally and on the server and load/resume them through Mobius UI.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • An Area Coverage Plan (ACP) has been created and exported.<br> • The exported objective plan has been loaded into Mobius (server load or local load).<br> • The exported objective database table (CSV files) is accessible for verification.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running with export/import functionality enabled.<br> • User access to the plan dropdown, local file browsing, and data-export interface.<br> • Ability to extract downloaded ZIP files containing database tables (e.g., MowingPlans.csv, ExportedObjectiveLoaded.csv).<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest Mobius Client and Server environment.<br> • File system access for saving and loading plans locally.<br> • Database export tools built into Mobius.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • ACP saved locally and on the server.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • ExportedObjectiveLoaded.csv contains a valid, correct plan name.<br> • Plan name must not be NULL, empty, or mismatched.<br> • File must be generated upon loading or resuming plan.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Creates a Plan and save the name<br>Load the Plan from the server<br>Load the plan from local<br>Open the database file and verify the plan name is correct, Expect that the plan names match</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
