  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-79 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213359"> VCU: Mower maintains speed over action points; slows only at turn initiation </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">02/04/2026 01:31:18 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-79</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371354</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Mower maintains speed over action points; slows only at turn initiation</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the mower does not slow down when passing over action points placed along a straight line, and that speed reduction occurs only when a turn is initiated, not during action-point traversal.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of VCU speed control when encountering action points during straight-line area-coverage execution.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Action points do not trigger speed reduction.<br> • Mower maintains a constant straight-line speed.<br> • Speed reduction occurs only when a turn begins.<br> • Behavior remains consistent across different speeds, action-point configurations, and turn angles.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and real-mower execution environments.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU builds support consistent straight-line speed control over action points.<br> • Action points placed along the straight path do not embed dynamic-speed modifiers (i.e., are non-dynamic action points).<br> • Turning events and deceleration events are correctly recognized and logged by the VCU.<br> • Speed values displayed in Mobius gauge panel accurately reflect commanded and measured speed.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Area-coverage plan configured with action points aligned along a straight track.<br> • Mower or simulator is checked into Mobius and capable of stable straight-line mowing.<br> • Vehicle is currently in motion approaching the action-point sequence.<br> • (Optional tip from steps) Bias adjustments applied to place action points perfectly in-line for clearer visualization.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Map loaded in Mobius with visible action points and a turn following the straight segment.<br> • Mobius gauge panel or telemetry display available for speed monitoring.<br> • Planner and implement libraries updated to latest version.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or real mower capable of area-coverage operation.<br> • One mower or simulator with functional implement and accurate speed reporting.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Straight-line action-point sequence.<br> • Various speed configurations and turn angles.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> •Mower maintains constant speed while passing over action points.<br> •Mower slows down only when initiating a turn.<br> •Behavior is consistent across repeated runs with varying configurations.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create new Offline plan&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Assign Plan&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Start Mower on new Plan, Plan created&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Plan assigned to mower&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;Mower is running plan<br>2: Check velocity on straight segment 1, VelocityCombined =3D 2.02<br>3: Check velocity on straight segment 2, VelocityCombined =3D 2.07<br>4: Check velocity on straight segment 3, VelocityCombined =3D 2.16<br>5: Check Velocity before the Corner segment, VelocityCombined =3D 2.16<br>6: Check Velocity in the Corner segment&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;*Expected to be slower, VelocityCombined &amp;lt; 1.97</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Failed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1886</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-80 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213360"> VCU: User-configurable arc-length threshold for arc-to-line conversion </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/09/2026 02:10:18 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-80</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371355</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: User-configurable arc-length threshold for arc-to-line conversion</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the VCU supports a user-configurable arc-length threshold used for determining when arcs should be converted into line segments during path execution.<br> • Confirm that default configuration preserves existing system behavior and does not disrupt mower operation when running plans or non-plan paths.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU when executing plans and non-plan paths under a configurable arc-length parameter.<br> • Validation focuses on ensuring that:<br> • Changing arc-length configuration does not break mower operation,<br> • Plans run to completion,<br> • Non-plan paths run without issue,<br> • Estops and image confirmations still function normally.<br> • Deep verification of arc-to-line conversion thresholds (e.g., breakpoint-based validation) is out of scope for mower-level testing and may require code-level instrumentation.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest VCU build includes a project-specific configuration parameter or startup-code option for arc-length threshold.<br> • Default arc-length value matches current production behavior for backward compatibility.<br> • Any user-configurable changes introduced do not affect safety, core mission execution, E-Stop behavior, or image-confirmation workflows.<br> • Mower or simulator behaves normally regardless of arc-length configuration unless explicitly broken in code.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mower or simulator available and checked into Mobius.<br> • Area suitable for running both ACPs and non-plan paths.<br> • Arc-length threshold configuration applied (default or test value).<br> • No uncleared E-Stops or blocking errors.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Mobius Server and Client connected to the vehicle.<br> • Ability to run both plan-based mowing operations and non-plan paths.<br> • Logging enabled to catch any unexpected VCU failures during execution.<br> • Image confirmation and E-Stop clearing workflows active.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or simulator supporting user-configurable arc-length parameter.<br> • Mower or sim capable of running long-duration plans without interruptions.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Area Coverage Plan (ACP).<br> • Non-plan path for execution.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • ACP executes normally and completes.<br> • Non-plan path executes without issue.<br> • Clearing E-Stops and image confirmations behaves normally.<br> • Mower continues to operate without unexpected failures, regardless of configurable arc-length value.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create a pland and asign with continue points<br>Start the mower on the plan<br>Verify that the mower didnt stop of that the plan didnt invalidate, Expect plan didnt validate</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1888</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-81 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213361"> Mobius: Planner-generated plans near bunkers are accepted unless they intersect bunker boundaries </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 05:04:43 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-81</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371356</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner-generated plans near bunkers are accepted unless they intersect bunker boundaries</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that Mobius accepts valid Area Coverage Plans generated by the Planner when mowing paths run close to bunker shapes, and rejects only those plans that intersect with the bunker map shape boundary.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of Mobius Server plan-validation logic when the Planner generates ACPs near bunkers.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Mobius does not overly restrict plans that are valid and remain outside bunker boundaries.<br> • Mobius does reject plans that enter or intersect the bunker polygon.<br> • Planner-generated paths near bunkers maintain reasonable clearance without deviating excessively from drivable fairway boundaries.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and Simulator environments using maps containing fairways, bunkers, and drivable areas.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server and Mobius Client builds include updated validation logic for bunker proximity.<br> • Planner correctly computes mowing paths near bunkers based on fairway geometry and drivable boundaries.<br> • Bunker map shapes are configured as non-drivable obstacles and are treated as hard constraints by Mobius.<br> • Simulated mower (or real mower) can execute the plan without performing dynamic obstacle avoidance.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client are installed and running.<br> • Sim Mower is checked in and available.<br> • A map exists (or is created) containing:<br> • At least one drivable area,<br> • One fairway,<br> • One bunker shape positioned ~10 feet from the fairway edge.<br> • Planner is able to generate ACPs for the selected fairway.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Map containing bunker, fairway, and drivable zones is loaded and published in Mobius.<br> • Planner libraries updated to support improved bunker-proximity logic.<br> • Mobius validation rules active for detecting bunker intersections.<br> • Simulation or mower environment allows full ACP execution.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or Simulator capable of running planner-generated ACPs.<br> • Map-editing or map-selection tools in Mobius for selecting shapes and generating plans.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Area Coverage Plan created for a fairway adjacent to a bunker.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Planner-generated plan follows fairway boundaries closely but does not enter the bunker.<br> • Mobius accepts the plan if it remains outside the bunker polygon.<br> • Mobius rejects the plan if path segments intersect bunker boundaries.<br> • Running the accepted plan executes to completion normally.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create a plan and asign with bunker shapes<br>Verify that Mobius accepts the plan when it plans to close to bunkers, Expect plan validated</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1890</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-82 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213362"> Mobius: Action points correctly placed on reverse segments of 3-point turns </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:34:17 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-82</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371357</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Action points correctly placed on reverse segments of 3-point turns</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the Planner places action points on the reverse segment of a 3-point turn when necessary to ensure complete mowing coverage and prevent skipped grass.<br> • Confirm that action-point placement correctly reflects the geometry of tight or awkward 3-point turns on fairways.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the Planner when generating area-coverage plans that require 3-point turns due to limited space or tight geometry.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Action points may be placed on a reverse track segment when needed for correct mowing coverage.<br> • Planner does not restrict action-point placement to forward segments only.<br> • Plans containing 3-pt turns execute without leaving unmowed strips.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and simulator-based environments where turn logistics affect implement actions.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU Planner components support placing action points on reverse segments.<br> • Fairway geometry produces one or more 3-pt turns due to turn-radius limitations or constrained approach spacing.<br> • Reverse-segment action points are allowed and do not violate other planner constraints.<br> • Mower simulator executes reverse and forward segments as planned.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client are installed and running.<br> • Simulator mower is checked in and capable of executing plans containing 3-pt turns.<br> • A map is available containing a fairway where the geometry forces tight or awkward turns, making a 3-point turn necessary.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Fairway map loaded into Mobius.<br> • Planner configured with logic supporting reverse-segment action-point placement.<br> • Logging and telemetry available to observe action-point positions and mower execution.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest VCU SIL/HIL build or simulator capable of:<br> • Reverse/forward movement transitions<br> • Executing 3-point turns<br> • Honoring action-point instructions on reverse segments<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Area Coverage Plan with one or more 3-pt turns in reverse.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Action points appear on reverse segments where needed.<br> • Planner does not skip coverage or misplace action points.<br> • Mower simulator runs the full plan without leaving uncut grass.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create and aissgn a plan with 3 points turns on a segment for revers<br>Verify that the mower runs the plan without offpath errors or other issues, Expect mower completes the plan.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1899</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-83 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213363"> Mobius: Resumed plans correctly identify remaining area and resume at correct path </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:41:06 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-83</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371358</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Resumed plans correctly identify remaining area and resume at correct path</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when an exported Area Coverage Plan (ACP) is resumed-after having been partially executed and then cleared-Mobius correctly identifies the remaining uncovered area and selects the appropriate resume path, even when the plan contains overlapping coverage rows.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of Mobius resume logic when executing ACPs with overlapping mowing paths.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Coverage history is preserved and considered during resume.<br> • Clearing and resuming an ACP results in accurate path selection.<br> • Mobius avoids resuming on the wrong overlapping path.<br> • The mower completes all remaining coverage without leaving unmowed gaps.<br> • Applies to mobile, desktop, SIL, HIL, and simulator environments.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server, Mobius Client, and VCU Planner builds support exported-objective resume logic.<br> • Resume-point computation correctly evaluates both path ordering and coverage history.<br> • Overlapping paths exist and are a realistic scenario in the map under test.<br> • Simulator or mower faithfully reports real-time coverage for history tracking.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Mobius Client running with access to exported objectives.<br> • Simulator placed and checked in on the map.<br> • ACP exists that contains overlapping paths within the fairway.<br> • Simulator or mower capable of executing and reporting coverage.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Map with overlapping coverage rows published in Mobius.<br> • Exported coverage objective available for loading.<br> • Coverage-history visualization enabled.<br> • Logging available to inspect selected resume points.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Latest simulator or SIL/HIL mower capable of:<br> • Running ACPs with overlapping rows<br> • Reporting coverage history<br> • Resuming coverage plans from exported objectives<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Exported ACP loaded from desktop or mobile.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Plan runs and generates partial coverage.<br> • Clearing and resuming the plan should select the correct resume path, even on overlapping rows.<br> • Mobius should complete the remaining coverage without missing areas.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create and aissgn a plan<br>Verify planned full coverage of remaining areas, Expect planning created full coverage</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1912</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-84 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213364"> VCU: pdVsData.audioVisualAlertDisable must not persist across restart </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">02/24/2026 01:33:58 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-84</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371359</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: pdVsData.audioVisualAlertDisable must not persist across restart</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Real mower powered on and checked into Mobius.<br> • Access to Mobius VCU Confirmation settings page.<br> • Audio and visual alert systems functional and enabled by default.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Mobius Server and Client connected to the mower.<br> • Logging or UI feedback available to observe alert behavior.<br> • Ability to restart the VCU cleanly.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower with VCU firmware supporting pdVsData parameters.<br> • Mobius Client for modifying DKS/VCU settings.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • DKS parameter: pdVsData.audioVisualAlertDisable<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Setting value to 1 disables audio and visual alerts (warning zone audio, beacon flashes).<br> • After VCU restart, the parameter resets to 0.<br> • Parameter value must not persist across restart cycles.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the DKS parameter pdVsData.audioVisualAlertDisable is not persistable, meaning any modification to its value resets to the default state (0) after the VCU restarts.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU confirmation settings and DKS parameter persistence.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Changing audioVisualAlertDisable to 1 disables audio/visual alerts during runtime.<br> • Restarting the VCU restores the parameter to its default 0 state.<br> • The parameter does not persist its modified value across power cycles.<br> • Applies to real-mower hardware only (per Preconditions).<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • VCU firmware correctly designates pdVsData.audioVisualAlertDisable as non-persistable.<br> • Default parameter state (0) is always correct upon VCU startup.<br> • The real mower environment accurately reflects both alert outputs and DKS values.<br> • Mobius displays confirmation settings consistent with VCU state.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Set DKS Value audioVisualAlertDisable to 1<br>Restart SIM<br>Verify AudioVisualState is Off, Expect AudioVisualState is Off and not persisting after SIM restart</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-193</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-85 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213365"> VCU: Deck Control Error triggers when commanded reel state mismatches actual state </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:56 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/09/2026 03:09:42 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-85</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371360</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Deck Control Error triggers when commanded reel state mismatches actual state</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the VCU raises a Deck Control Error when there is a mismatch between the commanded reel state (e.g., reels commanded down) and the actual reel state as reported by CAN messages, such as when physical transport hooks prevent the reels from lowering.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU deck-control subsystem when implement position feedback does not match commanded actions.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Commanded reel-down operations are correctly sent during an ACP or plan execution.<br> • CAN feedback reports that reels remain up (due to transport hooks).<br> • VCU detects this mismatch and triggers Deck Control Error.<br> • Error is surfaced to Mobius as expected.<br> • Applies to real-mower testing only (per Preconditions).<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest VCU firmware supports deck-control error detection via CAN state comparison.<br> • CAN messages accurately reflect reel-position sensors or actuator-state feedback.<br> • Transport hooks reliably prevent reels from lowering, creating a valid testable mismatch.<br> • Mobius correctly displays Deck Control Error alerts and logs.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Real mower available with functional reel-implement system.<br> • A plan exists (ACP or path-based) that commands reels to lower during execution.<br> • Transport hooks are installed and actively preventing reel movement.<br> • Mobius Server and Client connected to the mower.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Outdoor or controlled area where real mower motion is allowed.<br> • CAN communication active and reporting current reel states.<br> • Logging and error-display systems active in Mobius.<br> • Plan loaded and ready to command reel-down on startup or at first action point.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower with transport hooks to lock reels upright.<br> • Latest VCU build capable of Deck Control Error detection.<br> • Mobius Client for observing status, alerts, and error logs.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Plan with reel-down command.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Reels commanded down → Reels remain up due to hooks.<br> • CAN reports no movement toward commanded state.<br> • VCU triggers Deck Control Error.<br> • Mobius displays Deck Control Error notification.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Set sim.johnDeereMowerPlus1.xportSensor.overrideLeft and sim.johnDeereMowerPlus1.xportSensor.overrideRight to 0 and Set "JDMowerFeedback.override.proxSenseLtOffDnUp", "d" and "JDMowerFeedback.override.proxSenseRtOffDnUp", "d"<br>Assign Plan to Mower and Start Plan Execution<br>Verify expected deck states and that fault condition 0xC70E is present, Expect Decks to be Up and falut 0xC70E to be present</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1914</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-86 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213366"> Mobius: Action points at 3-point turns remain unchanged after plan import and confirmation </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/03/2026 12:56:51 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-86</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371361</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Action points at 3-point turns remain unchanged after plan import and confirmation</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that action points located at or near the apex of a 3-point turn are not deleted, moved, or altered when a plan is imported into Mobius and the user clicks Confirm.<br> • Ensure Mobius preserves the exact placement of action points defined in externally created or previously saved plans.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of Mobius during plan import, preview, and confirmation.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Action points located on or near a 3-pt turn apex remain intact.<br> • Mobius does not delete action points that lie directly on the turn vertex.<br> • Mobius does not reposition, distort, or create duplicate/weird action points during confirmation.<br> • Re-importing plans across multiple fairways consistently preserves action-point locations.<br> • Applies to Mobius Client/Server environments with plan-import capability.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server and Client builds include fixes for action-point deletion/reposition issues.<br> • Imported plans accurately contain action points at precise coordinates.<br> • 3-point turns are represented in the plan geometry exactly as produced by the Planner or external planning tools.<br> • Sim environment correctly displays action points but does not change plan geometry.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client are installed and running.<br> • Simulator (Sim) connected and ready.<br> • Ability to create or import plans containing 3-point turns.<br> • At least one fairway with geometry that produces 3-pt turns.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Plan builder or plan import interface available in Mobius.<br> • Plan preview mode shows all action points prior to confirmation.<br> • Confirmation logic active and capable of modifying plans (the behavior being tested).<br> • Logging available to capture any unexpected repositioning or deletion.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Mobius Client with plan import and confirm functionality.<br> • Simulator capable of loading ACPs and displaying action points.<br> • Plans with action points placed exactly at the apex of 3-pt turns (real or test-created).<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Multiple ACPs containing action points positioned at or near the pivot point of 3-pt turns.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • On import → Action point appears exactly where originally placed.<br> • On confirm → Action point does not disappear, move, or shift along the path.<br> • Repeated testing across multiple fairways shows consistent behavior with no "weird" or duplicated action points.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create a plan and assign with additional continue points<br>Gather the objective data points<br>Verify location of expected action points<br>Gather the objective data points<br>Verify location of expected action points, Expect All created action points still exist</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Failed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
