  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-87 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213367"> VCU: Adjusted Mobius Plan to Ensure final action point has sufficient buffer (&lt;3m fix) for end-of-plan reel lift </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/12/2026 01:02:18 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-87</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371362</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Adjusted Mobius Plan to Ensure final action point has sufficient buffer (&lt;3m fix) for end-of-plan reel lift</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when the final action point in an Area Coverage Plan (ACP) is too close to the end of the path (&lt; 3 m), the system correctly compensates by:<br> • Adding additional distance at the end of the plan, or<br> • Handling the final action as a 0m-buffered reel-lift, ensuring the mower can complete the path safely.<br><br>Confirm that the mower successfully completes the end-of-plan sequence: reels lift, mower continues forward ~3m, then stops and powers down the PTO/PTU without failing due to insufficient buffer.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU and Planner during the final segment of an ACP.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Final action point does not cause end-of-plan failure due to missing buffer distance.<br> • Mower performs correct reel-lift sequence even when the original plan's geometry places the final action point near the terminus.<br> • Additional end-segment buffer or corrected logic allows clean completion.<br> • Applies to real mower only-not reproducible in simulator.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius and VCU builds include updated logic for handling final action points &lt; 3m from path end.<br> • Planner or VCU automatically adjusts behavior (insert 3m segment or treat final lift as a 0m-buffer action).<br> • Reel-lift and PTU shutdown sequences follow configured safety and operational rules.<br> • End-of-plan behavior is observable via Mobius telemetry and mower behavior.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client are running.<br> • Real mower connected and operational (Sim will not reproduce issue).<br> • Area Coverage Plan created that includes cleanup laps and a final action point.<br> • ACP geometry results in a final action point close to the end of the plan (&lt; 3 m).<br><br>Environment:<br> • Real-world test space where a mower can complete an ACP.<br> • Mobius connected and displaying action points, reel state, and mission progress.<br> • Logging enabled to capture end-segment behaviors and PTU transitions.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower with functional implement and PTU.<br> • Latest VCU build with updated buffer-handling logic.<br> • Mobius Client for plan visualization and monitoring.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • ACP that includes a final action point (reel-lift) at or near the end of the cleanup lap.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Mower passes the final action point → reels lift to transport mode.<br> • Mower continues forward approximately 3 meters after reel lift.<br> • Mower comes to a complete stop and turns off the PTU.<br> • No end-of-plan failure occurs due to insufficient action buffer.<br> • Plan completes successfully.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create plan and assign<br>Verify last coverage segment is corrected, Expect the last action point to be adjusted</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Failed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1921</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-88 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213368"> Mobius: Planner avoids unnecessarily complex reversal paths when simpler forward connections exist </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:30:53 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-88</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371363</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner avoids unnecessarily complex reversal paths when simpler forward connections exist</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the Area Coverage Planner no longer produces unnecessarily complicated reversal segments (reverse → forward → reverse patterns) when planning fairways with complex geometry, and instead generates the simplest valid forward connection when one is clearly feasible.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of Mobius Planner when generating ACPs for fairways that have non-rectangular or irregular geometry.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Planner does not create excessive reverse maneuvers when a forward continuation would achieve the same coverage.<br> • Planner does not produce "loop-out → reverse → rejoin" patterns that leave the fairway unnecessarily.<br> • Trim distance penalties before and after zero do not create erratic or suboptimal turn connections.<br> • Multiple fairways and angles consistently produce simplified, logical turn behavior.<br> • Applies to SIL, HIL, ME-HIL, and simulator environments.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Updated Planner logic properly normalizes trim-distance evaluation, eliminating most previously observed problematic reversals.<br> • Fairway shapes tested include at least moderate complexity (non-oval, non-rectangular) to expose edge cases.<br> • Sim environment accurately displays Planner output, including reversal segments.<br> • Known problematic example cases (e.g., Barefoot 18B / Hole 12–6 reference) no longer produce undesired reversal paths.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running.<br> • Simulator (Sim) placed on a map.<br> • Map contains at least one fairway with complex geometry (non-simple shapes).<br> • Ability to adjust planning angle(s) to test different configurations.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Fairways loaded in Mobius with shapes that previously produced complicated turns.<br> • Planner libraries updated with IRD128-1704 fixes.<br> • Mobius UI able to display forward, reverse, and turn segments clearly.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Simulator or SIL/HIL mower capable of loading and displaying ACPs.<br> • Mobius Client with active planning tools.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • At least three different fairways, each tested with three different planning angles.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Planner generates continuous, logical forward connections where possible.<br> • No unnecessary reverse sections appear in ACP output.<br> • No paths leave the fairway boundary only to reverse and return to it when a simpler path exists.<br> • Complex turn sections should appear only when geometrically required.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create Plan and assign<br>Verify the number of reversals, Expected Tolerance: +-1 reversals</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1922</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-89 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213369"> VCU: Park brake must NOT engage during continuous 3-point turns </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/10/2026 11:26:17 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-89</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371364</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Park brake must NOT engage during continuous 3-point turns</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that during a continuous 3-point turn, the mower never engages the park brake, allowing the VCU to smoothly transition from forward → reverse → forward without causing an idle drop or interrupting mowing RPM.<br> • Confirm that the park brake does engage only when appropriate, such as during a pause, estop, or other complete stop condition-not during 3-pt turn transitions.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of the VCU during continuous turn maneuvers inside an Area Coverage Plan (ACP).<br> • Validation that:<br> • Park brake remains inactive through the entire 3-pt turn.<br> • Engine RPM remains at mowing-RPM levels and does not drop to low idle during the maneuver.<br> • Park brake engages normally only when the machine actually stops due to pause/estop.<br> • Applies to real-mower testing only.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • The VCU version under test (7ba26d56c2 or newer) contains updated logic for continuous 3-pt turns.<br> • The mower is capable of forward → reverse → forward transitions without requiring park-brake engagement.<br> • Engine RPM properly reflects park-brake state (idle drop =3D brake on).<br> • The plan used includes at least one valid 3-point turn.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Real mower available and operational.<br> • VCU firmware version 7ba26d56c2 or newer loaded on the vehicle.<br> • ACP loaded that includes at least one 3-pt turn.<br> • Mower checked in and ready to execute missions.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Outdoor or controlled space suitable for real mower movement.<br> • Mobius Server and Client connected to the mower.<br> • Ability to visually observe mower RPM behavior (UI, sound, or telemetry).<br> • Logging active for brake state, RPM, and turn transitions.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower with updated VCU firmware.<br> • Mobius Client for monitoring mode/alerts and turn execution.<br> • RPM observation method (vehicle display, Mobius telemetry, or audio confirmation).<br><br>Test Data:<br> • ACP containing a 3-point turn.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Park brake does NOT engage at any point during the 3-pt turn.<br> • Engine does NOT drop to low idle during forward → reverse → forward transitions.<br> • Park brake engages normally only if vehicle is paused, estopped, or otherwise fully stopped.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create Plan and assign, then start plan execution<br>Verify that the parking break is not on, Expected Parking break must not be engaged during continious 3-point turn</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1924</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-90 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213370"> VCU: Slip detection recovers from NaN and defaults to 0 </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:36:59 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-90</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371365</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Slip detection recovers from NaN and defaults to 0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that if the slip-calculation logic encounters a NaN (Not a Number) result, the VCU automatically recovers by defaulting the slip value to 0, ensuring stable behavior and preventing invalid slip states from propagating through the system.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of slip detection within the VCU when operating in conditions where slip may occur (wet grass, hills, mud, loose terrain).<br> • Validation that:<br> • Slip detection never reports NaN in Mobius or RTK settings.<br> • Any internal NaN calculation is safely converted to 0.<br> • Slip values observed after plan execution are always 0 or 1, never NaN.<br> • Applies to real-mower field testing only (per Preconditions).<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Slip detection is enabled in RTK settings and functioning.<br> • VCU firmware includes NaN-recovery logic.<br> • Slip values 0 and 1 represent valid internal states (boolean-style detection for "no slip" / "slip detected").<br> • Mobius UI or RTK settings page accurately reflects the slip state.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Real mower available and operational.<br> • Slip detection enabled in RTK settings.<br> • Mobius Server and Client connected to the mower.<br> • Test environment includes areas where slip is realistically possible (wet grass, hills, mud, etc.).<br><br>Environment:<br> • Outdoor or controlled area where mower can execute a complete fairway/plan.<br> • RTK and telemetry systems actively reporting slip values.<br> • Logging available to observe slip state transitions, if needed.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower with latest VCU build supporting slip-detection NaN-recovery logic.<br> • Mobius Client for viewing RTK slip-detection data.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Mower executes full ACP or fairway plan.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Mower completes plan normally.<br> • Slip detection value observed in RTK settings is 0 or 1.<br> • Slip detection must never show NaN.<br> • Any internal NaN slip calculation is overridden to 0 automatically.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create, assign plan, and run<br>Gather Pace.wheelslipControl.enable<br>verify: Pace.wheelslipControl.enable is enabled, Expected: That the wheel slip control is enabled and that wheel slip does cause a NaN error in the VCU</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1925</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
