  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-95 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213375"> VCU: Limit reverse-resume distance based on distance traveled since down relay turned off </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">03/09/2026 02:59:18 PM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-95</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371370</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Limit reverse-resume distance based on distance traveled since down relay turned off</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when resuming from a paused state, the mower does not reverse farther than the distance traveled since the reels were last lifted (down relay turned off).<br> • Ensure that limiting the reverse distance prevents the mower from backing off the fairway edge and eliminates scalping risk when pausing/resuming near boundary transitions.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Covers VCU logic governing motion sequencing during resume events immediately following a turn completion.<br> • Validates that reverse motion is constrained using the updated reverse-resume distance rule.<br> • Applies only to real mower testing and VCU firmware supporting IRD128-1717 updates.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Updated VCU firmware is installed, containing the new reverse-resume distance limit logic.<br> • Reels lift at the correct point during turn completion and resume logic accurately tracks distance traveled since that lift occurred.<br> • Mobius correctly issues pause and resume commands while the VCU enforces the new constraint.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Real mower available and checked in.<br> • Updated VCU firmware supporting the IRD128-1717 feature deployed.<br> • Area coverage plan (ACP) created on a fairway that includes turn maneuvers.<br> • Mower capable of running turn sequences and reporting reel-state transitions.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Real fairway or controlled test environment where mower transitions from turn arc back onto the fairway.<br> • Mobius Client and Server operational with normal command and telemetry flow.<br> • Logging enabled for:<br> • Reel relay state (down relay off/on),<br> • Reverse/forward transitions,<br> • Motion commands during resume.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower with functioning reel relay, turn logic, and reverse-motion capability.<br> • Mobius Client workstation or tablet for issuing pause/resume commands.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Area-coverage plan containing at least one turn where the mower exits and re-enters the fairway.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • When paused immediately after the mower re-enters the fairway, the mower does not reverse back off the fairway when resuming.<br> • Reverse motion is bounded by the exact distance traveled since reels lifted during the turn.<br> • No scalping occurs at the fairway edge upon resume.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create plan, assign, and begin executing the plan. Then pause<br>verify: that the mower doesn't reverse farther that the distance traveled since the reels were last lifted., Expected: mower doesn't reverse father than the distance traveled since the reels were last lifted.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1940</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-96 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213376"> Mobius: PTP Planner prevents paths through obstacles and non-drivable areas when importing plans </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:44:43 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-96</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371371</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: PTP Planner prevents paths through obstacles and non-drivable areas when importing plans</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that when a user imports a plan (from mobile or desktop), the Point-to-Point (PTP) planner correctly generates a navigation path to the fairway without planning through obstacles or outside drivable areas.<br> • Ensure the planner respects drivable boundaries and obstacle shapes for both initial navigation to the fairway and subsequent navigation between fairways.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Covers PTP planning behavior during plan import workflows.<br> • Validates path generation from:<br> • Vehicle's current position → fairway start point.<br> • Fairway A → Fairway B after confirming the first plan.<br> • Applies to real mower, simulation, and ME-HIL environments.<br> • Ensures consistency between mobile-imported plans and server-side validation.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • PTP planner has updated obstacle-avoidance logic for imported plans.<br> • Drivable areas, obstacles, and fairway boundaries are correctly defined in the map.<br> • Imported plan metadata includes valid starting positions and fairway references.<br> • Mobius server enforces navigation constraints and rejects illegal paths.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running.<br> • Real mower or simulator checked in and able to receive plan imports.<br> • Map containing:<br> • At least one fairway,<br> • Clearly defined obstacles,<br> • Drivable vs. non-drivable areas.<br> • Mobile-imported plan available or generated for the target fairway.<br> • Mower positioned so that a direct straight-line path to the fairway would intersect an obstacle or leave the drivable region.<br><br>Environment:<br> • PTP planning enabled and configured in Mobius.<br> • Valid map geometry supporting obstacle detection and driveable-area enforcement.<br> • Logging enabled for PTP path creation for verification of obstacle-avoidance logic.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower or simulator with PTP navigation support.<br> • Mobius Client or mobile app capable of importing area-coverage or path-builder plans.<br> • Map containing obstacles that enforce path rerouting.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Imported plan for Fairway A.<br> • Subsequent plan selection for Fairway B requiring navigation around obstacles.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Path from current mower location → Fairway A avoids obstacles and non-drivable areas.<br> • After confirming Plan A, navigation to Plan B also respects obstacle constraints.<br> • No straight-line shortcut through obstacles or map boundaries occurs.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create plan with obstacle, assign and begin execution.<br>verify: Plans with obstacles pass validation., Expected: Plans created on mobile that are importet pass validation.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1946</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-97 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213377"> VCU: Fix Payload Buffer Error at End of Path Assignments </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:42:26 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-97</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371372</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Fix Payload Buffer Error at End of Path Assignments</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the system no longer triggers a Payload Buffer Error at the end of each assignment or path segment.<br> • Confirm that the correct end-of-path action type is being inserted by the planner so the VCU does not reach an incomplete or invalid payload boundary condition.<br> • Ensure that all assignments complete cleanly without unexpected buffer underflow or missing-action conditions.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of Mobius Planner and VCU action-handling logic at the termination of assignments.<br> • Validation that:<br> • End-of-path payload requirements are satisfied by planner-generated actions,<br> • No extraneous buffer-related errors occur,<br> • Normal area coverage and path-builder plans complete without reporting payload faults.<br> • Applies to SIM and HIL environments; real mower optional but beneficial for regression.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Planner has been updated to insert a proper end-of-path action (rather than relying on artificially extended path distance).<br> • VCU firmware supports correct interpretation and execution of this new action type.<br> • Payload Buffer Error observed previously was unintended behavior, not a valid safety fault.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running with updated planner libraries.<br> • Simulator connected and able to execute assignments.<br> • At least one area coverage plan or path-builder plan available that includes multiple assignments, ideally where payload buffer errors were previously reproduced.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Standard Mobius environment with action sequencing and assignment execution enabled.<br> • Planner output logging enabled to confirm end-of-path action types.<br> • Simulator capable of reporting buffer or payload-related VCU errors.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Simulator running latest VCU build that includes Payload Buffer fix.<br> • Mobius Client capable of loading and executing ACP or PB plans.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Any ACP or Path Builder plan containing at least one assignment boundary where end-of-path actions must be executed.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • No Payload Buffer Error occurs at the conclusion of any assignment.<br> • End-of-path actions are present in the plan data and are executed cleanly.<br> • Plan runs to completion with no erroneous buffer events.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create plan with obstacle, assign and begin execution.<br>verify: Plans completes without a Payload buffer error., Expected: No Payload buffer error</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1970</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-98 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213378"> Mobius: Planner: Has VCU-provided hazard and warning zone dimensions for planning </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:33:18 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-98</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371373</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner: Has VCU-provided hazard and warning zone dimensions for planning</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that Mobius and the Planner correctly consume and apply the vehicle-dimension values provided by the VCU via DKS for calculating hazard zones, warning zones, and path-planning boundaries.<br> • Ensure that all plans generated in Mobius use the updated dimensional parameters so that hazard/warning envelopes match the new ODOA (Obstacle Detection &amp; Avoidance) system requirements.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Integration between Mobius, Planner, and VCU dimension data.<br> • Validation that the following VCU-provided DKS values are read, stored, and used during planning:<br> • pdVsData.mowerDim.controlPointToVehicleFrontDistanceMeters<br> • pdVsData.mowerDim.controlPointToVehicleRearDistanceMeters<br> • pdVsData.mowerDim.frontTrackingOffsetMeters<br> • pdVsData.mowerDim.hazardZoneSizeMeters<br> • pdVsData.mowerDim.mowVehicleWidthBladeToBladeMeters<br> • pdVsData.mowerDim.mowVehicleWidthMotorToMotorMeters<br> • pdVsData.mowerDim.rearTireOutsideEdgeTrackWidthMeters<br> • pdVsData.mowerDim.transportVehicleWidthMeters<br> • Applies to all planning modes that rely on vehicle dimensions: area coverage, boundary following, transport routing, and ODOA-enabled safety margins.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • VCU has been updated to publish all dimension variables reliably via DKS.<br> • Mobius Client retrieves and stores these values before plan generation.<br> • Planner version under test supports consuming these parameters and applying them to hazard/warning zone geometry.<br> • No legacy/mismatched dimension defaults override VCU-provided values.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running and connected to a mower (real or simulator).<br> • VCU firmware updated with IRD128-1894 dimension-export functionality.<br> • Planner and Mobius builds support use of DKS-dimension parameters.<br> • Mower (or simulator) checked in and reporting current DKS values.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Standard mowing map containing at least one fairway or test area where hazard/warning zone geometry is visible or exportable.<br> • Logging enabled to inspect dimension data flow from VCU → Mobius → Planner.<br> • Environment supports generating both ACP and PTP plans for comparison.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower or simulator capable of exposing dimensional DKS values.<br> • Mobius Client workstation.<br> • Current Planner release consuming hazard/warning zone dimensions.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Any area coverage plan or transport plan generated after Mobius retrieves dimensional values from the VCU.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Dimensions displayed in Mobius match those published by VCU.<br> • Planner-generated plans reflect appropriate hazard and warning zone sizes.<br> • No outdated or default values are used.<br> • Visual or logged properties of hazard/warning zones align with DKS values.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create plan with specific vcu-dimentions for hazard and warning zones<br>verify: Plans supply dimentions to the VCU by checking: pdVsData.mowerDim.controlPointToFrontVehicleEdgeDistanceMeters …, Expected: Plans generated in Mobius supply the dimentions to the VCU.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1975</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
