    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-99 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213379"> Mobius Server: Stability during mower reboot events (prevent server crash) </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:57 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:32:15 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-99</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371374</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius Server: Stability during mower reboot events (prevent server crash)</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the Mobius Server remains stable and does not crash when a mower (or simulator) is rebooted, repeatedly connected, or disconnected.<br> • Confirm that server-side handling of reboot events, reconnections, and session teardown is robust and fault-tolerant.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Server-side stability and connection-management logic during mower reboot cycles.<br> • Validation includes:<br> • Mower or simulator reconnection behavior,<br> • Handling of session resets,<br> • Proper cleanup of stale or partially initialized connections.<br> • Applies to all environments: SIM, HIL, ME-HIL, and real mower.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Latest Mobius Server build includes updated connection and reboot-handling logic.<br> • Simulator accurately replicates mower reboot/disconnect/reconnect behavior.<br> • Network conditions are stable and not contributing to artificial failures.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server running.<br> • Mobius Client open and connected.<br> • Simulator available and capable of repeated connect/disconnect cycles.<br> • No existing server faults or resource-limit issues before test.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Standard Mobius configuration with logging enabled.<br> • Environment must allow simulator reboot or connection cycling.<br> • Ability to observe server health metrics (logs, crash reports, restart behavior).<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Simulator that supports connect/disconnect operations.<br> • Mobius Client workstation.<br> • Mobius Server with crash reporting enabled.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Repeated simulator connections and disconnections over a sustained period (≥15 minutes).<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Server remains stable the entire time.<br> • No crashes, forced restarts, or unhandled exceptions.<br> • Simulator reconnects cleanly after each cycle.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Start Mobius Server<br>Start the simlator <br> Restart the Simulator repeat 11 times<br>verify: Server does not crash, Expected: Mowers/SIM can reboot and not cause the server to stop responding or crash. SIM's still check in.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1978</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-100 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213380"> VCU: Refactor Transport and Cross-Cut Dwell Times </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:42:50 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-100</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371375</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Refactor Transport and Cross-Cut Dwell Times</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the refactored dwell-time logic separates transport-enter dwell and cross-cut-enter dwell into independent timing controls.<br> • Confirm that reel-movement actions (up/down) and velocity-change actions can interrupt each other safely without producing a Deck Control Error.<br> • Ensure that reel actuation behaves predictably even when multiple action points occur in rapid succession along the same path.<br><br>Scope:<br> • VCU action-sequencing and dwell-time scheduling during path execution.<br> • Behavior when:<br> • Reels transition from transport → cross-cut mode,<br> • Reels transition from cross-cut → transport mode,<br> • Velocity change action points occur between reel actions.<br> • Applies to real-mower execution only (SIM cannot fully validate reel dwell timing).<br> • Covers deck-control reliability and proper interruption handling.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • VCU firmware under test contains the IRD128-1917 refactor for dwell-time separation.<br> • Reels support immediate interruption of dwell periods without generating erroneous deck control errors.<br> • Action points created in Mobius correctly serialize reel and velocity commands.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Client connected to a real mower.<br> • Ability to create a custom path in Path Builder or equivalent workflow.<br> • VCU firmware updated with dwell-time refactor.<br> • Mower functional with reliable reel-actuation hardware.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Test area with at least 50 ft of drivable space.<br> • Deck control feedback available in telemetry (reel positions, deck errors, velocity).<br> • No active errors on the mower prior to test start.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower running the updated VCU firmware.<br> • Mobius Client for creating paths and issuing commands.<br> • Mower capable of processing SBRmower Up Dist and Dn Dist reel-control commands.<br><br>Test Data:<br><br> • Custom path with:<br> • Length ≥ 50 ft,<br> • Three action points:<br> • Action Point 1 (Dn Dist): Lower reels,<br> • Action Point 2: Velocity change (3.5 mph → 3.5 mph to trigger mid-sequence behavior),<br> • Action Point 3 (Up Dist): Raise reels.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Mower transitions between dwell types (transport ↔ cross-cut) smoothly.<br> • Velocity-change action point does not cause a deck control error during reel-lowering dwell.<br> • Actions are allowed to interrupt each other safely.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Expect this to be the timing between dwell state controls, Assign Path and run<br>Verify Deck control error doesn't persist longer than 10 seconds</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1987</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-101 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213381"> Mobius: Offline Planner: Save and Load Plans (Break dependency from current plan) </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:40:14 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-101</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371376</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Offline Planner: Save and Load Plans (Break dependency from current plan)</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that Offline Planning in Mobius can save, load, and restore planning progress independently of the active runtime plan.<br> • Confirm that all elements of an offline plan-including vehicle information, lane/swath parameters, and boundary laps-persist across Mobius Client restarts.<br> • Validate that the Offline Planning Organizer can create, load, and delete plans without relying on or affecting the current operational plan in Mobius.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Offline planning workflow only (not live operational planning).<br> • Functionality validated includes:<br> • Creation of Offline Plans,<br> • Saving plans to the server,<br> • Reloading plans after client restart,<br> • Restored visibility of planning progress (vehicles, lanes, swaths, parameters),<br> • Deletion of plans and confirmation that they are removed from the organizer.<br> • Applies to Mobius Server + Mobius Client environments.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Offline planning now uses a dedicated planning engine, separate from the active mission planner.<br> • The server stores all required plan metadata, including:<br> • Vehicle selection and heading,<br> • Lane generation settings,<br> • Swath parameters,<br> • Boundary lap parameters,<br> • Partially completed progress in the Offline Planner UI.<br> • Mobius Client retrieves saved plan data upon reconnecting to the server.<br> • No synchronization logic is dependent on "current plan" or mission state.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server running with Offline Planning features enabled.<br> • Mobius Client connected to server.<br> • Map containing fairways available for Offline Planning.<br> • Server has permissions to persist planning artifacts.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Offline Planning tab enabled and accessible.<br> • Server configured to store and retrieve Offline Planning JSON/state files.<br> • Stable network between Client and Server to support save/load operations.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Mobius Client workstation.<br> • Mobius Server with persistent storage enabled (file or DB depending on implementation).<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Fairway selected for planning.<br> • Vehicle asset chosen for path generation.<br> • Offline plan containing:<br> • Lane Generation output,<br> • Swath Generation output,<br> • Boundary Lap Generation output,<br> • Connect Swaths progression.<br><br>Expected Behavior:<br> • Plans created in Offline Planning persist after closing/reopening Mobius Client.<br> • Planning progress (up to swath generation) reloads correctly, including:<br> • Vehicle selection, location, and heading,<br> • Lane parameters,<br> • Swath parameters,<br> • Boundary lap parameters.<br> • Deleted plans do not reappear after client restart.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create Plan, save, then load a plan<br>Verify plans save and load, Expect that a plan is saved and a new one is loaded</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1988</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-102 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213382"> Mobius: Planner: Area Coverage Shape implemented as a standalone plugin </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">02/01/2026 01:28:01 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-102</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371377</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner: Area Coverage Shape implemented as a standalone plugin</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the Area Coverage Shape has been successfully separated into its own plugin, which can be enabled or disabled via the plugins.json configuration files on both Mobius Client and Server.<br> • Ensure full backward compatibility so existing maps, imported maps, and previously planned coverage missions continue to function without change.<br> • Confirm that all area coverage workflows-including shape creation, import/export, planning, and loading plans-operate correctly when the plugin is active.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Behavior of Mobius Client and Server when using the new standalone Area Coverage Shape Plugin.<br> • Validation includes:<br> • Map imports and exports involving area coverage shapes,<br> • Creation of new coverage shapes and other map features (fairways, obstacles, bunkers),<br> • Plan creation, export, import, and execution,<br> • Offline Planner compatibility,<br> • Plugin visibility in the Mobius plugins list.<br> • Applies to SIM and real mower environments (SIM sufficient for this case).<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Area Coverage plugin is installed and configured via plugins.json.<br> • No regressions introduced in map-editing or coverage-planning capabilities.<br> • Import/export formats support area coverage shapes whether or not the plugin is enabled.<br> • Planner fully supports area coverage shapes originating from the plugin interface.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running with plugin support enabled.<br> • At least one map available for import testing.<br> • At least one previously created coverage plan available for import testing.<br> • Mower simulator available and able to load plans.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Map Editor enabled with support for area coverage shape plugin.<br> • Offline Planner available and functional.<br> • Plugin list visible from the Mobius Client Plugin Page.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Mobius Server with plugin architecture enabled.<br> • Mobius Client capable of editing maps, running Offline Planner, and loading plans.<br> • Mower SIM for verifying plan load/execution behavior.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • A map containing area coverage shapes.<br> • A second map to be imported for testing.<br> • A previously exported area coverage plan.<br><br>Expected behavior:<br> • Maps load and import correctly with area coverage shapes preserved.<br> • New shapes (bunkers, obstacles, fairways) appear correctly after publishing.<br> • Coverage plans generate and export without issues.<br> • Imported plans load and run correctly via SIM.<br> • Area Coverage plugin appears in Mobius plugins list on both Client and Server.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create Plan with elements known with the Area coverage Shape<br>Verify plan loads and has the spacific name from the plugins, Expect that the new Area Coverage Shape (OfflinePlanning) is in the plugin</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1995</td>
     </tr>
