  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-103 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213383"> Mobius: Map:Disengage Shape implemented as standalone plugin (formerly Waterway Shape) </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:37:15 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-103</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371378</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Map:Disengage Shape implemented as standalone plugin (formerly Waterway Shape)</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the former Waterway Shape has been refactored into a standalone Disengage Shape Plugin, and that Mobius correctly loads, interprets, and handles these shapes during planning.<br> • Confirm backward compatibility so older maps containing waterway shapes seamlessly load and behave as Disengage Shapes, with no regression in coverage-planning behavior.<br> • Ensure new disengage shapes can be created and used for planning in the same manner as historical waterway shapes.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Plugin-based map shape handling in Mobius Client and Server.<br> • Validation includes:<br> • Loading maps containing legacy waterway shapes and converting them to disengage shapes,<br> • Editing maps and adding new disengage shapes,<br> • Planner behavior when using shapes to create reel raise/lower action points,<br> • Plugin visibility and correct enablement in plugins.json.<br> • Applies to area coverage, fixed crop, and mowing planners that rely on disengage zones.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Disengage Shape plugin is properly installed and active via plugins.json on both Mobius Client and Server.<br> • Legacy waterway shapes map cleanly to disengage-shape semantics.<br> • Planner logic that previously handled waterway shapes now handles disengage shapes identically.<br> • No dependency remains on the deprecated waterway implementation.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client installed with plugin architecture enabled.<br> • At least one legacy map that contains a Waterway Shape (may require exporting from older Mobius versions).<br> • Ability to edit maps and create new shapes.<br> • Simulator or real mower checked in for planning validation.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Map Editor enabled with disengage-shape plugin active.<br> • Plugin list visible in Mobius settings.<br> • Planner capable of generating ACP plans that interact with disengage shapes.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Mobius Client workstation.<br> • Mobius Server with plugin-enabled configuration.<br> • Mower simulator or real mower for plan execution testing.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Legacy map containing a waterway shape.<br> • A newly created disengage shape.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Legacy waterway shape loads as a disengage shape.<br> • New disengage shape behaves identically to legacy shape.<br> • Planner creates reel raise/lower action points at intersections with swaths.<br> • Disengage Shape Client and Server plugins appear in plugin list.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create Plan Assign <br>Verify plan loads and has the water way shape, Expect that DisengageShape is in the plugin</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1997</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-104 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213384"> Mobius: Planner: Bunker Shapes Must Be Non-Drivable </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:36:03 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-104</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371379</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner: Bunker Shapes Must Be Non-Drivable</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that bunker shapes are treated as non-drivable obstacles, preventing the vehicle from entering or passing through them during execution of waypoint plans or area coverage plans.<br> • Confirm that if a bunker shape is added to an existing map after a plan is created, the vehicle will still respect the updated geometry and halt before entering the bunker.<br> • Validate that the system raises the correct stopping condition, such as "Stopped by Proximity Monitor (0x10004)", when approaching a bunker.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Planner and VCU interaction with bunker geometry.<br> • Behavior when:<br> • Running a plan that did not originally include a bunker in the route,<br> • Editing the map to introduce a bunker intersecting the planned path,<br> • Executing the plan after map changes.<br> • Applies to simulator and real-mower execution.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Updated Planner and VCU logic treat bunker shapes as completely non-drivable.<br> • Proximity Monitor detects bunker boundaries the same way it treats obstacles or no-go zones.<br> • Map edits take effect on the vehicle's next execution cycle once the map is republished.<br> • Older Mobius versions (before this fix) allowed driving through bunkers, providing a regression baseline.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running.<br> • Simulator or real mower connected and checked in.<br> • A fairway map available for planning.<br> • Ability to edit and republish maps.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Desktop Mobius Client with Planner and Proximity Monitor enabled.<br> • Map Editor configured to add bunker shapes.<br> • Logging enabled for proximity-related stopping events.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Mower simulator or real mower.<br> • Mobius Client workstation.<br> • Map Editor with bunker-shape creation capability.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • A waypoint or ACP plan created before adding the bunker.<br> • Updated map with a bunker inserted across the previously planned path.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Map publishes successfully with the new bunker.<br> • When executing the plan, the mower follows the drivable portion of the path.<br> • Upon approaching the bunker boundary, the mower halts and triggers "Stopped by Proximity Monitor (0x10004)".<br> • Under no circumstances does the mower enter or traverse the bunker area.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create Plan with bunker, Assign, begin exection of plan<br>Verify that the bunker shape is no longer drivable, Expect that bunker shapes are not drivable</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-1998</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-105 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213385"> VCU: Tune Exit Transport Parameters to Prevent Deck Control Errors </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:41:08 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-105</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371380</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Tune Exit Transport Parameters to Prevent Deck Control Errors</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that updated exit-transport tuning parameters prevent the mower from triggering a Deck Control Error when transitioning from Transport Mode → Cross-Cut/Mowing Mode.<br> • Confirm that reel-lowering behavior during exit transport is smooth, predictable, and within acceptable timing tolerances defined by the updated VCU logic.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Applies to VCU reel-control and deck-control management during the transition out of transport mode.<br> • Ensures that updated exit-transport timing/dwell parameters:<br> • Prevent premature deck-state evaluation,<br> • Allow the reels to lower without conflict,<br> • Avoid false Deck Control Errors.<br> • Real mower testing required (SIM cannot fully validate deck hardware signals).<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • VCU includes IRD128-2082 exit-transport tuning changes.<br> • Reel actuation hardware is functioning normally.<br> • Mobius Client provides live feedback of deck control state for verification.<br> • No unrelated deck errors are active during test execution.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Real mower available and fully operational.<br> • Updated VCU firmware with tuned exit transport parameters installed.<br> • Mobius Client (desktop or mobile) connected and displaying mower state.<br> • A fairway plan exists that begins with the mower exiting transport mode and lowering reels to start mowing.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Outdoors or safe test area where normal mowing behavior can occur.<br> • Stable network connection between mower and Mobius.<br> • Deck control telemetry visible in Mobius, including reel state and deck-control error indicators.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower with reel/lift hardware active.<br> • Mobius Client (desktop or mobile).<br> • Plan capable of initiating reel-lowering at the start of mowing.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Any area coverage or fairway plan where the mower transitions out of transport mode into active mowing.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Reels lower smoothly as the mower begins mowing.<br> • No Deck Control Error is thrown during or immediately after reel lowering.<br> • Mower continues mowing without interruption.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create Plan with bunker, Assign, begin exection of plan. Then lower reels<br>Verify no deck control error was present, Expect new exit transport parameters no longer throw a deck control error</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-2016</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-106 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213386"> Mobius: Offline Planner: Clockwise/Counterclockwise Cleanup Lap Direction Not Working </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:46:35 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-106</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371381</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Offline Planner: Clockwise/Counterclockwise Cleanup Lap Direction Not Working</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the Offline Planner correctly respects the user-selected Direction parameter-CLOCKWISE or COUNTERCLOCKWISE-when generating cleanup laps for a fairway.<br> • Confirm that the cleanup lap geometry matches the selected rotational direction and that the issue where both directions produced the same output is fully resolved.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Offline Planner boundary-lap generation only.<br> • Behavior under test includes:<br> • Direction selection in the Boundary Lap configuration,<br> • Correct orientation of cleanup lap output,<br> • Consistency between CLOCKWISE and COUNTERCLOCKWISE settings,<br> • Behavior across multiple fairways and planner sessions.<br> • Applies exclusively to Offline Planning (not live planning).<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Planner tool is updated with IRD128-2162 fixes.<br> • CoverageRequestPlan.json contains correct and up-to-date fairway geometry.<br> • Planner logic now honors direction selection when generating boundary laps.<br> • No caching or stale-plan artifacts interfere with direction-setting behavior.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running.<br> • Offline Planner accessible from Mobius Client.<br> • A fairway with a valid CoverageRequestPlan.json available.<br> • Latest planner tool installed, including the direction-selection fix.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Offline Planning mode with full access to Boundary Lap settings.<br> • Planner logs or plan-visualization tools available to confirm lap orientation.<br> • No other shapes (disengage, waterway, no-go zones) interfering with boundary-lap geometry.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Mobius Client workstation.<br> • Planner tool installed with IRD128-2162 correction.<br> • Fairway map for testing CLOCKWISE vs. COUNTERCLOCKWISE lap generation.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Cleanup lap configuration with Direction set to:<br> • CLOCKWISE (first run),<br> • COUNTERCLOCKWISE (second run).<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • When Direction =3D CLOCKWISE → cleanup lap geometry rotates clockwise around the fairway.<br> • When Direction =3D COUNTERCLOCKWISE → cleanup lap geometry rotates counterclockwise.<br> • Results should clearly differ in orientation and confirm correct directional planning.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create Plan with bunker, Assign, begin exection of plan. Then pase and clear plan <br>Verify proper directions CLOCKWISE and COUNTERCLOCKWISE in the geometry, Expect When Direction =3D CLOCKWISE → cleanup lap geometry rotates clockwise around the fairway.<br>Expect When Direction =3D COUNTERCLOCKWISE → cleanup lap geometry rotates counterclockwise.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-2022</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
