  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-107 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213387"> Mobius Server: Log VAI Connection State in Database </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:38:34 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-107</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371382</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius Server: Log VAI Connection State in Database</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the VAI Service Connection State is correctly logged in the Mobius database for all vehicles checked into the server.<br> • Confirm that VAI-related warning messages do not flood server logs, ensuring stable server performance and clean log output.<br> • Validate that exported raw database data includes an accurate, timestamped history of VAI connection states.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Mobius Server logging behavior for VAI communication state.<br> • Database export pipeline and generation of .csv files related to VAI connection tracking.<br> • Applies to real mowers and simulators checked into Mobius.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Mobius Server includes IRD128-2288 logging improvements.<br> • VAI connection heartbeat/status messages are throttled or filtered to prevent log flooding.<br> • The Raw Data export includes a correctly formatted VAI connection state file for each vehicle.<br> • At least one vehicle is checked into Mobius during the test window.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server running with database logging enabled.<br> • Mobius Desktop Client connected to the server.<br> • At least one real mower or simulator currently checked in to Mobius.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Stable network connection between mower and Mobius.<br> • Database export functionality available under Settings → Database.<br> • Ability to access and open .csv files after export.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Mobius Desktop Client<br> • Mobius Server<br> • Real mower or simulator checked in and communicating with VAI<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Raw Data export covering a timeframe during which a mower was checked in.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • A "VAI Service Connection State" .csv file is included in the export.<br> • File contains timestamped entries reflecting VAI connection state (connected, disconnected, reconnects, etc.).<br> • Server logs do not contain excessive or redundant VAI warning messages.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Start the mower<br>Verify that the VAI connection state was logged to the database, Expect that the VAI connection state get's logged every time</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-2036</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-108 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213388"> Mobius: Planner: Mowing-Specific Planner for Importing Offline Planning Plans </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:37:33 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-108</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371383</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner: Mowing-Specific Planner for Importing Offline Planning Plans</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the new mowing-specific planner can successfully import and validate plans created in Offline Planning.<br> • Confirm that plans generated offline can be loaded onto a vehicle (real mower or simulator) and run using standard Mobius validation and execution pathways.<br> • Ensure that invalid plans are correctly flagged and that errors are presented to the user before execution.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Integration between Offline Planning and the new mower-specific runtime planner.<br> • Validation that:<br> • Offline plans load onto vehicles,<br> • Standard Mobius validators execute without regression,<br> • Errors surface appropriately for malformed or incompatible plans,<br> • Valid plans execute end-to-end in Mobius.<br> • Applies to both real mowers and simulators, though SIM is typically used for functional testing.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Mowing-specific planner is implemented and functional.<br> • Offline Planning exports plans in a format consumable by the mowing planner.<br> • Mobius Client correctly lists offline-created plans in the fairway plan selector.<br> • Validators (geometry, constraints, safety checks) are active and integrated with imported plans.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running.<br> • Offline Planner accessible and able to generate fairway plans.<br> • Simulator or real mower connected and checked in.<br> • Fairway map corresponding to the offline-generated plan available in Mobius.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Offline Planning enabled and configured.<br> • Mowing-specific planner active in Mobius.<br> • Logging enabled for plan validation and load events.<br> • No existing plan conflicts or stale assignments on the mower/sim.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Mobius Desktop Client.<br> • Mobius Server.<br> • Simulator or real mower capable of running imported offline plans.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Offline-generated plan for a fairway.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Plan imports without formatting or validation errors.<br> • Confirming the plan loads it onto the mower.<br> • Running the plan produces no execution failures.<br> • Any invalid plans display meaningful user errors.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create, Assign, and execute a plan<br>Verify the plan executes completely, Expect that the plan executed against the offline planning module</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-2043</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-109 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213389"> Mobius: Planner: Add Continue Points to New Mowing Objectives (Offline Planning Integration) </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:31:15 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-109</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371384</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius: Planner: Add Continue Points to New Mowing Objectives (Offline Planning Integration)</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that offline-planned mowing objectives support continue points, allowing the operator to begin execution at any selected location within the plan.<br> • Ensure Mobius correctly reloads the objective to include only the remaining segments from the user-selected start point.<br> • Confirm that continue-point selection behaves consistently across multiple fairways and plan geometries.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Applies to offline-generated mowing plans imported into Mobius.<br> • Testing includes:<br> • Display of continue-point selection UI (thumb icon),<br> • Drag-and-drop selection to any point along the plan path,<br> • Partial plan regeneration from selected start point,<br> • Correct execution from the newly selected start position.<br> • Supports both SIM and real mower usage, though SIM is recommended for large-scale validation.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Offline planning is already generating multi-part mowing objectives compatible with continue-point features.<br> • Mobius Client includes UI support for continue point selection.<br> • Mower or simulator can handle resuming operations from mid-plan without errors.<br> • Planner regenerates the remaining path based on the continue-point selection.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client running.<br> • Simulator connected and checked in.<br> • Offline Planner accessible and capable of generating mowing objectives.<br> • A fairway map available for plan generation.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Mobius Client build that includes continue-point functionality.<br> • Stable connection between mower/simulator and Mobius.<br> • Logging enabled for objective updates and path regeneration.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Mobius Client workstation.<br> • Mobius Server.<br> • Simulator (or real mower for validation).<br> • Offline Planner.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • An offline-generated plan containing multiple segments.<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Continue-point UI appears when selecting an offline plan.<br> • Dragging the thumb icon to any point in the plan regenerates the objective beginning at that point.<br> • Regenerated plan excludes already completed sections and preserves correct sequencing.<br> • Works consistently across several fairways and various continue-point selections.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create, Assign, and add continue Point Segments<br>Verify that new point can be ran from, Expect mower executes from any new added points</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-2046</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-110 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213390"> Mobius Server: Default Notification Toasting Disabled for All Notification Levels </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:03:58 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:33:41 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-110</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371385</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mobius Server: Default Notification Toasting Disabled for All Notification Levels</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that Mobius no longer automatically toasts notifications to the user by default.<br> • Confirm that all notification categories (Information, Warning, Critical) have toast settings disabled unless explicitly enabled by the user.<br> • Ensure notification behavior differs correctly between Mower Builds and Internal Builds, per updated design requirements.<br><br>Scope:<br> • Mobius Client notification settings.<br> • Behavior under test:<br> • Default toast toggle states for each notification level,<br> • Correct application of settings after default configuration files are reset,<br> • Ensuring toasts do not appear unless the user manually enables them.<br> • Validation applies to desktop Mobius Client across all build types.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • Mobius Server and Client support reading and regenerating notification settings from the default configuration.<br> • Deleting the NotificationSettings files forces Mobius to initialize fresh default notification preferences.<br> • The updated logic differentiates correctly:<br> • Mower Build: All categories default to toast OFF.<br> • Internal Build: Only Information defaults to toast OFF; Warning and Critical remain configurable.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Server installed with access to system configuration folder:<br> C:\ProgramData\MobiusServer\Settings\NotificationSettings<br> • Mobius Client installed (Mower Build or Internal Build).<br> • Ability to navigate to Mobius Settings → Notifications.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Windows host machine running Mobius Client.<br> • File Explorer access to Server settings folder.<br> • Notification tab available in Mobius Client Settings.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Mobius Desktop Client (Mower or Internal Build).<br> • File system access to delete notification settings files.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Default notification configuration generated after deleting:<br> • NotificationSettings*.json<br> • Expected behavior:<br> • Mower Build:<br> • Information → Toast OFF<br> • Warning → Toast OFF<br> • Critical → Toast OFF<br> • Internal Build:<br> • Information → Toast OFF<br> • Warning → Toast ON (default)<br> • Critical → Toast ON (default)<br> • No notifications toast automatically unless explicitly enabled by user.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Start mobius Server and delete the notifications<br>Verify .json files contain the Toast \ Fales key value pair, Expect Notification settings to persist in the json file settings</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
