  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-117 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213397"> VCU: Local Confirmation Implementation — Phase 1 (IRD128-2350) </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:04:00 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:39:00 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-117</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371392</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: Local Confirmation Implementation — Phase 1 (IRD128-2350)</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify Phase 1 implementation of the new Local Confirmation flow in the VCU according to the approved design diagram.<br> • Confirm that Local Confirmation timeout behavior, clearing logic, and estop interactions operate as defined.<br> • Validate telemetry interfaces required for Local Confirmation: timeout telemetry and clear-command telemetry.<br><br>Scope:<br> • VCU logic for Local Confirmation timeout, hazard-zone evaluation, and estop behavior.<br> • Telemetry items used for Local Confirmation (Inf: Local Confirmation Timeout, Cmd: Clear Local Confirmation).<br> • Interaction between auto/manual modes, hazard zone entry/exit, and timeout expiration.<br> • Applies to real mower hardware; simulator behavior acceptable where possible.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • VCU build includes IRD128-2350 Phase 1 Local Confirmation logic.<br> • Hazard-zone logic remains active, including errors 0xC708 (hard estop) and 0xC711 (soft).<br> • Telemetry values update in real time and are accessible through Mobius gauges or equivalent tools.<br> • Automated tests may use ODZones.override.vaiZHazard =3D 1 to simulate obstacle presence.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Desktop Client running.<br> • Real mower preferred; simulator acceptable for limited verification.<br> • Access to telemetry gauges or VcuTelemetry tool to observe Local Confirmation fields.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Safe area where obstacles can be placed/removed from mower hazard zone.<br> • Stable comms between mower and Mobius Desktop Client.<br> • Telemetry panel or VCU console available for error observation and timeout monitoring.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower with updated VCU implementing Local Confirmation Phase 1.<br> • Mobius Desktop Client.<br> • Method for placing a physical obstacle or enabling ODZones.override.vaiZHazard.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Telemetry items:<br> • Inf: Local Confirmation Timeout<br> • Cmd: Clear Local Confirmation<br> • DKS parameter:<br> • ODZones.localConfirmationTimeoutSec<br> • Hazard-zone override:<br> • ODZones.override.vaiZHazard =3D 1<br><br>Expected behavior:<br> • Local Confirmation Timeout telemetry becomes nonzero only when hazard is cleared and auto mode is active.<br> • Hard estop hazard (0xC708) appears when expected and clears only under correct Local Confirmation conditions.<br> • Timeout value respects DKS configuration changes.<br> • Clearing Local Confirmation before timeout reaches zero clears the estop hazard; clearing after timeout has expired does not.<br> • Switching to manual mode always clears the estop hazard.<br> • Local Confirmation Timeout drops to zero immediately when a clear command is issued.<br> • Restarting the mower in auto mode results in hard estop hazard (0xC708) being set.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Set up interfaces to Local Confirmation telemetry items using Mobius gauges or a telemetry tool:<br>a. Inf: Local Confirmation Timeout<br>b. Cmd: Clear Local Confirmation<br>Gauges become available in Mobius.<br><br>Start the mower in manual mode.<br><br>Place an object in the hazard zone.<br>Verify:<br> • No 0xC708 or 0xC711 estop hazard errors are set.<br> • Inf: Local Confirmation Timeout =3D 0.<br>Automated tests use ODZones.override.vaiZHazard =3D 1.<br><br>Remove the obstacle from the hazard zone.<br><br>Switch to auto mode.<br>Verify:<br> • Inf: Local Confirmation Timeout begins counting down from ODZones.localConfirmationTimeoutSec (default 20 sec).<br> • Hard estop hazard 0xC708 is set.<br><br>Switch to manual mode.<br>Verify 0xC708 clears.<br><br>Change ODZones.localConfirmationTimeoutSec (e.g., to 30 sec) and repeat verification to confirm configurability., In auto mode, before the timeout reaches 0, command “Cmd: Clear Local Confirmation” =3D Clear.<br> Verify:<br> • 0xC708 clears after VAI acknowledgement delay.<br> • Inf: Local Confirmation Timeout immediately resets to 0.<br><br> Place an obstacle in the hazard zone.<br> Verify:<br> • 0xC708 is set.<br> • Image is generated (if observable).<br> • Inf: Local Confirmation Timeout remains 0.<br><br><br> Remove the obstacle and issue Clear Local Confirmation.<br> Verify:<br> • 0xC708 remains set.<br><br> Switch to manual.<br> Verify 0xC708 clears.<br><br> Switch to Auto and wait for Local Confirmation Timeout to expire (reach 0).<br><br> Command Clear Local Confirmation.<br> Verify 0xC708 remains set.<br><br> Toggle to manual, then auto, and clear before timeout expiration.<br> Verify 0xC708 clears.<br><br> Switch to manual.<br> Verify 0xC708 clears.<br><br> Restart the mower in auto mode.<br> Verify 0xC708 is set on startup.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Assigned:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Priority:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"E39191" width=3D"80%">High</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>External ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">https://testlink.asirobots.com/linkto.php?tprojectPrefix=3DAG&amp;item=3Dtestcase&amp;id=3DAG-2082</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Legacy Keywords:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> <br> <br>
  </div>
  <div class=3D"Section1">
   <table class=3D"grid" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=3D"0" width=3D"100%">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td bgcolor=3D"f0f0f0" colspan=3D"2" valign=3D"top"><h3 class=3D"formtitle">LFWM2-VERTCA-118 <a href=3D"perspective.req?projectId=3D152&amp;docId=3D5213398"> VCU: VAI Removal of 90-Second Occlusion Timeout (IRD128-2520) </a>&nbsp; 
        <div class=3D"subText">
         Created: <font color=3D"336699">12/17/2025 03:04:00 PM UTC</font> &nbsp;Updated: <font color=3D"336699">01/28/2026 04:33:04 AM UTC</font>
        </div></h3></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Project ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">LFWM2-VERTCA-118</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Global ID:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">GID-3371393</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Name:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">VCU: VAI Removal of 90-Second Occlusion Timeout (IRD128-2520)</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"" width=3D"80%">Draft</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Description:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Objective:<br> • Verify that the legacy 90-second occlusion timeout has been fully removed from VAI simulation in both the VCU and Holodeck environments.<br> • Confirm that no estop or fault condition is triggered after 90 seconds of pause due to an occlusion-based timeout.<br> • Ensure plan loading, execution, and pause behavior continue functioning normally without unexpected hazard or occlusion errors.<br><br>Scope:<br> • VCU and VAI hazard/occlusion timeout logic.<br> • Applicable to both real mower hardware and simulator (Holodeck or VAI sim).<br> • Includes validation of pause/resume behavior and estop logic in absence of the deprecated timeout.<br><br>Assumptions:<br> • IRD128-2520 changes are applied in the VCU firmware and Holodeck/VAI simulation layers.<br> • No fallback or hidden occlusion timer still exists in the code path.<br> • Hazard logic and estop triggers continue functioning normally aside from the removed timeout.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Scheduled Release:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Mower Version 4.0</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Setup:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Preconditions:<br> • Mobius Desktop Client running and connected to a mower or simulator.<br> • Firmware version deployed that includes removal of the 90-second occlusion timeout.<br> • A valid plan available for loading and execution.<br><br>Environment:<br> • Mobius Desktop Client with stable connection to the mower or simulator.<br> • Safe area where a test pause can be conducted for 90+ seconds without obstacles or interruptions.<br><br>Equipment:<br> • Real mower or VAI simulator/Holodeck with updated firmware.<br> • Mobius Desktop Client capable of monitoring estop state and execution status.<br><br>Test Data:<br> • Any valid fairway or test plan.<br> • Expected telemetry: No occlusion timeout fault, no estop due to timeout.<br><br>Expected behavior:<br> • Plan loads successfully and mower/sim begins execution normally.<br> • After pausing and waiting 90 seconds, no occlusion timeout estop occurs.<br> • Mower remains in paused state without transitioning to estop due to elapsed time.<br> • No warnings or errors referencing occlusion timeout appear in Mobius, logs, or telemetry.</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Steps:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">1: Create plan, Assign, begin executing the plan<br>When deck value changes pause the operations, Verify estop state <br>Expect Verify no occlusion timeout</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Case Status:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Passed</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Test Run Results:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%"></td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automated:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"ffffff" width=3D"80%">Yes</td>
     </tr>
     <tr bgcolor=3D"ffffff">
      <td width=3D"20%"><b>Automation Tool:</b></td>
      <td bgcolor=3D"$myLookupColor" width=3D"80%">TestPlatform</td>
     </tr>
